(220, '3', 'QUANTITATIVE ANALYSIS IN EDUCATIONAL RESEARCH I', 'AHE 611', 2, 'Foundational course to methods and statistics used in quantitative educational research. Examines data analysis, statistical procedures, and interpretation of results within postsecondary environments.', ''),
(221, '3', 'RESEARCH PERSPECTIVES IN EDUCATION', 'AHE 612', 2, 'Research perspectives, how they are influenced by worldviews, and how these worldviews influence research.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Community College Leadership (2076).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(222, '3', 'RESEARCH ANALYSIS AND INTERPRETATION IN EDUCATION', 'AHE 613', 2, 'Critical analysis of scholarly studies in education from a variety of research perspectives.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Community College Leadership (2076).'),
(223, '3', 'ADVANCED RESEARCH METHODS IN EDUCATION', 'AHE 614', 2, 'Selected topics in research methods as appropriate for research perspectives in education. May be repeated.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Community College Leadership (2076).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(224, '3', 'RESEARCH ISSUES', 'AHE 615', 2, 'A core course in the College of Education\'s doctoral program that focuses on research issues.', 'Prerequisites: (AHE 612, 613 and 614).A minimum grade of C is required in AHE 612, AHE 613 and AHE 614.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Community College Leadership (2076).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(225, '3', 'QUANTITATIVE ANALYSIS IN EDUCATIONAL RESEARCH II', 'AHE 616', 2, 'Develop conceptual and practical understanding of research and evaluation in higher education. Course topics include basic statistics, survey design, data analysis, and assessment issues. As an advanced statistics course, students will have the opportunity to apply concepts and gain direct research experience by conducting an original research project.', 'Prerequisite: AHE 611.A minimum grade of C is required in AHE 611.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(226, '3', 'QUALITATIVE ANALYSIS IN EDUCATIONAL RESEARCH', 'AHE 618', 2, 'Introduces learners to a variety of qualitative research perspectives and methodologies. Participants will examine these approaches by critiquing a scholarly article containing qualitative methods; formulating qualitative questions; writing a short proposal; collecting, coding, and analyzing data; and writing a final synthesis paper.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Adult and Higher Education (2075).'),
(227, '3', 'LEADERSHIP IN STUDENT SERVICES: ST/ LEADERSHIP IN STUDENT SERV', 'AHE 621', 2, 'Exploration of significant issues in design and delivery of student services in community college and higher education settings. Group discussion, model building, problem posing, issues analysis, and theory applications are employed. Students will reflect on current and future practices in student services, including emerging approaches to leadership.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Adult and Higher Education (2075).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(228, '3', 'HISTORY OF HIGHER EDUCATION', 'AHE 638', 2, 'Surveys American higher education across 200-plus years of American history, with a specific emphasis in this section on the American community college.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(229, '3', 'HIGHER EDUCATION ADMINISTRATION', 'AHE 640', 2, 'Current leadership and management theories and models, systems of organization, patterns of internal and external governance, and issues in institutional planning and advancement in higher education.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Adult and Higher Education (2075).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(230, '3', 'ORGANIZATION THEORY-HIGHER EDUCATION', 'AHE 643', 2, 'An introduction to organizational theory (OT). The texts allow us to explore how systems thinking is applied to our world, and how we can use it to better understand the nature of human social engagement. Both OT and living systems theories are deeply associated with improvement and change theories in higher education settings and business.', ''),
(231, '3', 'ETHICAL PRACTICE', 'AHE 645', 2, 'Reviews major ethical theories with an emphasis on practical applications related to community college professional practice.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Adult and Higher Education (2075).'),
(232, '3', 'INSTRUCTIONAL LEADER I', 'AHE 653', 2, 'A core course in the College of Education\'s doctoral program. Introduces major theories, theorists, and theoretical principles that will assist the learner in the understanding and development of systemic frameworks for instructional leadership.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(233, '3', 'RESEARCH PERSPECTIVES IN FOUR-YEAR HIGHER EDUCATION', 'AHE 672', 2, 'An overview of the extensive research related to four-year colleges and universities, with an emphasis on the role of research in understanding and interpreting the nature of higher education. Explore research epistemologies, theories, and approaches related to social science and higher education, and how these ideas influence worldview and subsequent research. Identify a significant research topic/problem statement which will carry forward into the second year research courses in moving toward the dissertation topic for research related to four-year higher education.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Leadership in Higher Education (2077).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(234, '3', 'RESEARCH INTERPRETATION IN FOUR-YEAR HIGHER EDUCATION', 'AHE 673', 2, 'Critical analysis and interpretation of journal articles and scholarly research related to a problem statement in four-year higher education organization, learning, and/or leadership. Refinement of Sections 1 (Research Focus and Problem Statement) and II (Manuscript and Literature Review) of a Dissertation Proposal in four-year higher education.', 'Prerequisite: AHE 672.A minimum grade of C is required in AHE 672.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Leadership in Higher Education (2077).'),
(235, '3', 'ADVANCED RESEARCH METHODS IN FOUR-YEAR HIGHER EDUCATION', 'AHE 674', 2, 'Identification and evaluation of an appropriate quantitative or qualitative study focused on four-year higher education. This includes a requirement that students demonstrate the ability to analyze and interpret data associated with their research question(s) as identified in their research proposal and that they outline the methodology that will be used to answer their research question(s)/proposal.', 'Prerequisite: AHE 673.A minimum grade of C is required in AHE 673.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Leadership in Higher Education (2077).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(236, '3', 'FOUR-YEAR HIGHER EDUCATION RESEARCH ISSUES', 'AHE 675', 2, 'Finalize a dissertation proposal related to a research question on four-year education institutions that reflects research epistomologies, theories and approaches. Develop a dissertation draft for review by the student\'s dissertation committee outlining: (a) Purpose of the student\'s study and its significance within the context of research on four-year colleges and universities, (b) Review of related literature on the specific topic of the dissertation, and (c) Design of the dissertation study.', 'Prerequisite: AHE 674.A minimum grade of C is required in AHE 674.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Leadership in Higher Education (2077).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(237, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO AEROSPACE ENGINEERING', 'AAE 210', 0, 'Topics will include the engineering fundamentals of aeronautics and astronautics, including an introduction to aerodynamics, propulsion, structures, orbital mechanics and mission planning. Current industry practices in aerospace vehicle specifications, manufacturing, flight testing and certification will be presented.', 'Prerequisite: ENGR 211.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 211.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
(238, '4', 'SPACE SYSTEMS ENGINEERING', 'AAE 412', 0, 'Introduction to space systems engineering. Topics will include the fundamentals of astronautics, orbital mechanics and trajectory design, flight dynamics, guidance and navigation, stability and control of spacecraft. Rocket propulsion concepts, including chemical rockets (liquid, gas and solid propellants), hybrid rocket engines and modern advances in satellite power systems will be discussed. Current design practices in space systems engineering will be emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: (ME 317 or 317H) and (ME 373 or 373H).A minimum grade of C is required in ME 317, ME 317H, ME 373 and ME 373H.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Mechanical Engineering (321) or Aerospace Engineering (905).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(239, '1', 'FOUNDATIONS OF THE AIR FORCE PART I', 'AS 111', 0, 'The introduction to the Air Force mission and organization. Featured topics include Air Force dress and appearance stand standards; military customs and courtesies, Air Force heritage, overview of the Department of the Air Force, and Air Force core values. Basic oral and written communication will be assessed.', ''),
(240, '1', 'FOUNDATIONS OF THE AIR FORCE PART II', 'AS 112', 0, 'Second part of the introduction to the Air Force mission and organization. Featured topics include Air Force career opportunities, Air Force benefits, military communication skills, Air Force installations, and look at the basic characteristics of war. Basic oral and written communication will be assessed.', ''),
(241, '1', 'FOUNDATIONS OF THE AIR FORCE PART III', 'AS 113', 0, 'Third part of the introduction of what the Air Force is about and what the Air Force has to offer. Featured topics include basic leadership, team building, interpersonal skills, diversity in the Air Force, and the oath of office and commissioning. Basic oral and written communication will be assessed.', ''),
(242, '1', 'LEADERSHIP LABORATORY', 'AS 120', 0, 'Cadets learn officership, leadership, drill and ceremony, and customs and courtesies. Lab. Graded P/N.', ''),
(243, '1', 'THE EVOLUTION OF AIR AND SPACE POWER 1860-1945', 'AS 211', 0, 'Study of the development of air power, concepts, and doctrine from its beginnings to the end of World War II. Historical examples examined include balloons, dirigibles, Wright Brother\'s first flight, and the role of air power in World War I and II. Oral and written communication skills will be assessed.', ''),
(244, '1', 'THE EVOLUTION OF AIR AND SPACE POWER 1945-1990', 'AS 212', 0, 'Study of the development of air power, concepts, and doctrine during the Cold War. Historical examples examined include the Berlin Airlift, nuclear deterrence, and the role of air power employment in the Korean and Vietnam conflicts. Oral and written communication skills will be assessed.', ''),
(245, '1', 'THE EVOLUTION OF AIR AND SPACE POWER 1991-2025', 'AS 213', 0, 'Study of the factors contributing to the development of air power, concepts, and doctrine from the Persian Gulf War in 1990 to the present and beyond. Historical examples examined include the air campaigns used in the Gulf War, Kosovo crisis, Operations Enduring Freedom, Iraqi Freedom, and the Global War on Terrorism. Oral and written communication skills will be assessed.', ''),
(246, '1', 'LEADERSHIP LABORATORY', 'AS 220', 0, 'Cadets are placed in element leadership positions in order to know and comprehend the Air Force concepts of command, discipline, tradition, and courtesies. Lab. Graded P/N.', ''),
(247, '1', 'SPECIAL TOPICS IN AIR FORCE STUDIES', 'AS 299', 0, 'Supervised individual work.', ''),
(248, '6', 'FIELD TRAINING', 'AS 304', 0, 'Four-week field training supplements campus courses in developing leadership and discipline. Mission, organization, and functions of an Air Force base; marksmanship, survival, and physical training; aircrew and aircraft indoctrination; orientation on specific opportunities in career fields. Conducted at an Air Force base. Graded P/N.', ''),
(249, '3', 'LEADERSHIP FUNDAMENTALS, TEAM BUILDING AND PROBLEM SOLVING', 'AS 311', 0, 'Emphasis on leadership and management fundamentals, team building and problem solving. Case studies are used to examine leadership and management situations as a means of demonstrating and exercising practical application of the concepts being studied. Unique exercises will be utilized to emphasize team building and problem solving. Oral and written communication skills will be assessed.', '');
