(648, '1', 'SEMINAR: SEMINAR/ BROWN BAG 2019', 'AEC 607', 2, '', ''),
(649, '4', 'ADVANCED MICROECONOMIC THEORY I', 'AEC 611', 2, 'A rigorous development of the theory of consumption and production, with emphasis on duality.', 'Prerequisites: (AEC 512 and 513).A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 512 and AEC 513.'),
(650, '4', 'ADVANCED MICROECONOMIC THEORY II', 'AEC 612', 2, 'A rigorous extension of the theory of the consumer and firm to aggregate and heterogeneous populations, decision making under uncertainty, and related game theory concepts.', 'Prerequisite: AEC 611.A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 611.'),
(651, '4', 'ADVANCED ECONOMETRICS I', 'AEC 625', 2, 'Emphasizes the basic theory underlying the main types of estimators used in econometrics, as well as their application in empirical research. Includes derivation, properties, and application of method of moments, maximum likelihood, ordinary and generalized least squares, and instrumental variables estimators, statistical inference and hypothesis testing, and model building and specification analysis. Provides the necessary foundation for estimation techniques covered in AEC 626. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisite: AEC 525.A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 525.'),
(652, '4', 'ADVANCED ECONOMETRICS II', 'AEC 626', 2, 'Extensions to the generalized linear regression model are considered: discrete choice, limited dependent variable, panel data, and simultaneous equations models, and new solutions to identification problems. Strong applied orientation, emphasizing problems of data measurement, model selection and specification.', 'Prerequisite: AEC 625.A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 625.'),
(653, '3', 'SUSTAINABLE DEVELOPMENT', 'AEC 640', 2, 'Surveys research on the quantitative economic analysis of sustainable development, with an emphasis on integrated assessment methods and models and their application to agriculture and rural development policy, agricultural technology impact assessment, and climate change impact assessment.', 'Prerequisites: AEC 611, 612 and 625.A minimum grade of D- is required in AEC 611, AEC 612 and AEC 625.'),
(654, '3', 'ADVANCED TOPICS IN DEVELOPMENT ECONOMICS', 'AEC 643', 2, 'Introduces students to key issues in the economics of development and equips them with the theoretical and empirical tools required to conduct advanced research in these topics.', 'Prerequisites: AEC 613 and 626.A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 613 and AEC 626.'),
(655, '3', 'ADVANCED ENVIRONMENTAL ECONOMICS', 'AEC 652', 2, 'Interrelationships of natural resource use and the environment; applied welfare and benefit-cost analysis; externalities and pollution abatement; non-market valuation of resources; property rights; legal and social constraints; policy approaches.', 'Prerequisites: (AEC 513 or AREC 513) and (AEC 525 or AREC 525).A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 513, AREC 513, AEC 525 and AREC 525.'),
(656, '3', 'EMPIRICAL ENVIRONMENTAL AND RESOURCE ECONOMICS', 'AEC 653', 2, 'Introduces empirical methods at the current frontiers of research in environmental and resource economics. General topics may include the identification of non-market values, revealed and stated preference methods, environmental policy evaluation, equilibrium sorting models, and climate econometrics.', 'Prerequisites: AEC 513 and 525.A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 513 and AEC 525.'),
(657, '3', 'MEDIA STORYTELLING', 'AJ 311', 0, 'Introduction to community journalism, with a focus on developing storytelling methodologies for a variety of media in firsthand reporting praxis.', 'Prerequisite: WR 121.A minimum grade of B is required in WR 121.'),
(658, '3', 'ADVANCED MEDIA STORYTELLING', 'AJ 312', 0, 'Continued praxis in journalistic storytelling, with an emphasis on developing intensive hard news stories and photojournalistic essay packages through reporting government agencies.', 'Prerequisite: AJ 311.A minimum grade of B is required in AJ 311.'),
(659, '3', 'PROFESSIONAL PRACTICES IN APPLIED JOURNALISM', 'AJ 313', 0, 'Faculty, staff and students connect to generate in-depth critiques of polished journalistic projects, culminating in the production and distribution of a best practices job kit.', 'Prerequisites: AJ 311 and 312.A minimum grade of B is required in AJ 311 and AJ 312.'),
(660, '1', 'INTERNSHIP', 'AJ 410', 0, 'Students seeking to obtain the Applied Journalism Minor must complete three sections of AJ 410 Internship, to include reporting, production and/or editorial duties at Orange Media Network (OMN).', ''),
(661, '3', 'MEDIA LAW AND ETHICS', 'AJ 490', 0, 'Exploring case studies and other analyses germane to the most relevant and pressing legal and ethical issues in contemporary journalism.', 'Prerequisite: AJ 311.A minimum grade of B is required in AJ 311.'),
(662, '4', 'DESIGN OF ELECTRICAL AND ILLUMINATION SYSTEMS FOR BUILDINGS', 'ARE 352', 0, 'Design of electrical and illumination systems in buildings, including consideration of energy usage.', 'Prerequisite: CEM 471.A minimum grade of C is required in CEM 471.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Architectural Engineering (826).'),
(663, '4', 'DESIGN OF HVAC SYSTEMS FOR BUILDINGS', 'ARE 353', 0, 'Design and engineering of heating, ventilating, and air conditioning (HVAC) systems in buildings, including consideration of energy usage and indoor environmental conditions.', 'Prerequisite: CEM 472.A minimum grade of C is required in CEM 472.'),
(664, '4', 'ADVANCED BUILDING CONSTRUCTION METHODS', 'ARE 451', 0, 'Advanced building construction methods, including integration of building components in building envelopes. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisite: CEM 442.A minimum grade of C is required in CEM 442.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Architectural Engineering (826).'),
(665, '4', 'SPECIAL TOPICS: ST/ DESIGN OF ELE', 'ARE 599', 2, '', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Civil Engineering (3060).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(666, '1', 'ART ORIENTATION', 'ART 100', 0, 'Introduction to the study of art and career options in fine arts, graphic design, photography, and art history.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Applied Visual Arts (859), Art (880) or Art History (881).'),
(667, '3', '*INTRODUCTION TO THE VISUAL ARTS', 'ART 101', 0, 'An introductory lecture course using visual materials with emphasis on methods and motivations that generate the visual experience, both past and present. (FA) (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(668, '4', '2-D CORE STUDIO', 'ART 115', 0, 'Studio course that introduces the visual language, the elements of design, and the principles of organization. Emphasizes skills, concepts, and problem solving in the areas of two-dimensional design and color.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Digital Communication Arts (473)Art and Design (478)Pre-Graphic Design (479)Graphic Design (779)Applied Visual Arts (859)Art (880)'),
(669, '4', '3-D CORE STUDIO', 'ART 117', 0, 'Studio course examining three-dimensional design elements and their spatial organization. Emphasizes innovative problem solving and exposure to varied media. Gives students a sound conceptual basis to apply to more advanced media-oriented courses.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Digital Communication Arts (473)Art and Design (478)Studio Art (748)Graphic Design (779)Applied Visual Arts (859)Art (880)'),
(670, '4', 'DIGITAL CORE STUDIO', 'ART 121', 0, 'An introductory studio art class using computers in the visual arts. Project-based exploration of digital imaging, layout, 3-D rendering, and video. Examination of the impact of digital technology on the visual arts from contemporary and historical perspectives.', ''),
(671, '4', 'DRAWING CORE STUDIO', 'ART 131', 0, 'Introductory studio course in drawing techniques with emphasis on developing skills in perception and visual organization. Lec/studio.', ''),
(672, '1', 'SPECIAL STUDIES: SS/ STUDIO FOR ART 100', 'ART 199', 0, '', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Applied Visual Arts (859) or Art (880).'),
(673, '4', 'SPECIAL STUDIES: ST: DESIGN TOOLS AND TECHNIQUE', 'ART 199', 0, '', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(674, '4', 'SPECIAL STUDIES: ST: GRAPHIC DESIGN I', 'ART 199', 0, '', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(675, '3', '*INTRODUCTION TO WESTERN ART: PREHISTORY TO THE HIGH MIDDLE AGES', 'ART 204', 0, 'A survey of the painting, sculpture, architecture, and decorative arts of Europe and the Mediterranean between the Paleolithic period and the eleventh century. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(676, '3', '*INTRODUCTION TO WESTERN ART: GOTHIC TO BAROQUE', 'ART 205', 0, 'A survey of the painting, sculpture, architecture, and decorative arts of Europe between the late Middle Ages and the seventeenth century. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(677, '3', '*WESTERN ART: 12TH-17TH CENT: *INTRO TO ART HISTORY- WESTERN', 'ART 205', 0, 'A survey of the painting, sculpture, architecture, and decorative arts of Europe between the late Middle Ages and the seventeenth century. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(678, '3', '*INTRODUCTION TO WESTERN ART: NEOCLASSICISM TO CONTEMPORARY', 'ART 206', 0, 'A survey of painting, sculpture and other visual arts in the Western world from the late eighteenth century to the present. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(679, '3', '*INTRODUCTION TO ASIAN ART', 'ART 208', 0, 'Introduces the distinctive, yet related, aesthetic traditions of South and Southeast Asia, Inner Asia, and East Asia. It focuses on architectural sites, sculptures, and paintings from prehistory to the present. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(680, '3', '*HISTORY OF WESTERN ARCHITECTURE', 'ART 210', 0, 'A survey of buildings and architectural thought in the West from antiquity to the twentieth century; focuses on major periods and movements of architectural history by examining building types, patrons, materials, building traditions, structural innovations and other critical aspects inherent to architecture. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(681, '4', 'COLOR IN THE VISUAL ARTS', 'ART 215', 0, 'Studio course following ART 115 and ART 117 that examines the properties of colors and their interaction. Emphasizes problem solving and the experimental use of color.', 'Prerequisite: ART 115.A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 115.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(682, '4', 'INTRODUCTION TO TIME-BASED ART', 'ART 222', 0, 'Introduction to time-based media using the computer as a tool. Studio art class developing skills in video art, sound art, performance, and other time-based digital arts. Exploration of sequential, experimental, historical, and contemporary themes and the role of the audience in time-based art.', 'Prerequisite: ART 121.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 121.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(683, '4', 'DRAWING II/FIGURE', 'ART 234', 0, 'Drawing from the life model with emphasis on skill and conceptual awareness as well as anatomical consideration.', 'Prerequisite: ART 131.A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 131.'),
(684, '4', 'DIGITAL PHOTOGRAPHY', 'ART 263', 0, 'Introductory course in digital photography. Focus on creation of photographic images in series format. Technical camera operation will be emphasized as well as basic photographic composition, use of photographic editing software, historical grounding, and discussions of contemporary issues in photography. Students must have the use of a digital single lens reflex camera (DSLR) or mirrorless camera (with viewfinder and fully manual controls).', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Digital Communication Arts (473)Art and Design (478)Pre-Graphic Design (479)Studio Art (748)Graphic Design (779)Applied Visual Arts (859)Art (880)Art History (881)'),
(685, '3', '*PHOTOGRAPHY: HISTORY, TECHNOLOGY, CULTURE AND ART', 'ART 264', 0, 'Introduction to the history of photography through aesthetic, cultural and technical contexts. This course covers the history of photography and its technologies, photography in art, some photographers and their photographs and the purposes of photography. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(686, '4', 'PRINTMAKING I', 'ART 271', 0, 'Introduction to the basic processes of printmaking, with options among relief, lithography, intaglio, screen printing and monotype.', 'Prerequisites: ART 115 and 131.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 115 and ART 131.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Studio Art (748), Applied Visual Arts (859) or Art (880).'),
(687, '4', 'PAINTING I', 'ART 281', 0, 'Introductory studio course with emphasis on basic materials and techniques in painting. (FA)', 'Prerequisite: ART 131.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 131.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Studio Art (748)Graphic Design (779)Applied Visual Arts (859)Art (880)Art History (881)'),
(688, '4', 'SCULPTURE I', 'ART 291', 0, 'Studio course in basic materials and approaches used in sculpture; a foundation for further three-dimensional work. (FA)', 'Prerequisite: ART 117.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 117.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Studio Art (748)Graphic Design (779)Applied Visual Arts (859)Art (880)Art History (881)'),
(689, '3', '*EARLY CHINESE ART AND ARCHAEOLOGY', 'ART 310', 0, 'Introduces major forms of Chinese art from the Neolithic period to the Tang dynasty (618-907 CE) and related major archaeological finds. Stresses the materials and processes of making art, development of representational art, and the role of visual arts in an aristocratic and religious culture. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(690, '3', '*LATE CHINESE ART AND CULTURE', 'ART 311', 0, 'Introduction to the major forms of Chinese art and visual culture from the eleventh century to the early twentieth century. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(691, '3', '*CONTEMPORARY CHINESE ART', 'ART 312', 0, 'Introduces origins and development of contemporary Chinese art and visual culture in its domestic and global contexts. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(692, '3', '*ANCIENT GREEK ART', 'ART 320', 0, 'Focuses on the major artistic developments in Ancient Greece from the Middle Bronze Age to 31 BCE, and especially on the city-state of Athens during the Fifth Century. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(693, '3', '*ANCIENT ROMAN ART AND ARCHITECTURE', 'ART 321', 0, 'Survey of ancient Roman art and culture between the sixth century BCE and fifth century CE, covering principal media, styles, and subject matter. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(694, '3', '*MEDIEVAL ART AND ARCHITECTURE', 'ART 322', 0, 'Survey of the art and architecture of the major periods and cultures of Europe and the Mediterranean between the fourth and the fourteenth century. Traces salient developments in thought and material culture of western civilization. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(695, '4', 'DRAWING CONCEPTS', 'ART 331', 0, 'Studio course emphasizing drawing composition as an investigative, conceptualizing and communicative nonverbal language. Independent thinking, problem solving, and creative development encouraged.', 'Prerequisites: ART 131 and 234.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 131 and ART 234.'),
(696, '3', 'PROFESSIONAL PRACTICES FOR ARTISTS', 'ART 339', 0, 'Examination of relevant issues and realities facing working artists today through class discussion, critical readings, gallery visits, guest lectures and panel discussions. Development of professional practices appropriate for artists and the business of art include portfolio development, writing and presentation skills, grants, contracts, exhibition opportunities and marketing strategies.', 'Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Junior or Senior.'),
(697, '4', 'DARKROOM PHOTOGRAPHY I', 'ART 340', 0, 'Studio course in black-and-white film exposure and development, and printing in the darkroom. The medium of silver-based black-and-white photography is explored as a communication mode and art form. Historical, conceptual, technical and legal aspects of traditional wet processing are surveyed. Access to a single lens reflex (SLR) film camera is required. Course fee.', ''),
(698, '4', 'DARKROOM PHOTOGRAPHY II', 'ART 341', 0, 'Improving silver-gelatin printing and photographic presentation techniques. Emphasis on furthering creative visual language and individual photographic project development. Studio and lecture course. Student must supply a medium format or 35mm single lens reflex (SLR) film camera. Lec/studio.', 'Prerequisite: ART 340.A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 340.'),
(699, '4', 'INTERMEDIATE PHOTOGRAPHY', 'ART 345', 0, 'Emphasis is on both technical and aesthetic expression of digital color photography, from initial image capture, color management to finished print along with color symbolism and composition. Exploration of narrative, sequencing and image-series concepts. Introduction to contemporary color photographers. Studio.', 'Prerequisite: ART 263.A minimum grade of C+ is required in ART 263.'),
(700, '4', 'PHOTOGRAPH: STUDIO LIGHTING', 'ART 347', 0, 'Practical studio class surveying the basic principles and application of light in the creation of photographs. The development of craft and technique inside the studio will be emphasized but formal and conceptual considerations related to light and photography will also be explored.', 'Prerequisite: ART 263.A minimum grade of C is required in ART 263.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Studio Art (748)Applied Visual Arts (859)Visual Arts (878)Art (880)Art History (881)Photography (893)'),
(701, '4', 'VIDEO ART', 'ART 349', 0, 'Studio course in video art and time-based media projects. Emphasis on experimental approaches to video art in a contemporary art context, linear and non-linear video production and the projection and screening of video art projects. Introduction to the history of video art as an art form. Lec/studio. CROSSLISTED as ART 349/NMC 349.', 'Prerequisites: ART 222 and 263.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 222 and ART 263.'),
(702, '4', 'PHOTOGRAPHY ON ASSIGNMENT', 'ART 350', 0, 'An introduction to shooting photographs on assignment. Students will create, edit, caption, and submit photographs for print publications, online media, and alternative/independent media venues. Students will experiment with text, audio slideshows, and other creative means of illustrating concepts and ideas. Also covered are history, law, and ethics of photojournalism.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman may not enroll.'),
(703, '4', 'INSTALLATION', 'ART 351', 0, 'Studio/lecture course designed to acquaint the student with the possibilities of using non-traditional means such as site, time, and interaction to communicate ideas.', 'Prerequisites: ART 291 and (minimum score of 1 in \'Fine Arts Portfolio Review\' or minimum score of 1 in \'Graphic Design Portfolio Revie\').A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 291.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(704, '3', '*CREATIVE COLLABORATION: DESIGNING AND BUILDING', 'ART 352', 0, 'Working in multi-disciplinary teams, design, implement, and document a piece of public art work or science museum display. Projects may be made of any media, but must demonstrate creativity both in the engineering used to create them and the technology and society message they convey. CROSSLISTED as ART 352/ENGR 352. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(705, '4', 'ALTERNATIVE PROCESSES IN PHOTOGRAPHY', 'ART 354', 0, 'Historical photographic printing methods in use today e.g., cyanotype, gum bichromate and more. Use of digital and analog negatives, mixing emulsions and coating paper by hand.', 'Prerequisites: ART 263 and 345.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 263 and ART 345.'),
(706, '4', 'THE PHOTOGRAPHIC BOOK', 'ART 355', 0, 'Practical studio course focusing on the photographic book in all of its forms. Use appropriated imagery as well as original imagery to create a variety of zines as well as soft and hardcover photo-books. Structure, form, materials, and layout will be discussed as well as content, sequencing, and physical construction. CROSSLISTED as ART 355/GD 355.', 'Prerequisite: ART 263.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 263.'),
(707, '3', '*PHOTOGRAPHY: ACTIVISM, AND SOCIAL CHANGE', 'ART 359', 0, 'Explores photography as an agent of social change through creative projects and topical discussions. Emphasis on the visual language, ethical considerations, and strategies employed by activist photographers that disrupt dominant ideologies and address institutionalized inequality and privilege in the United States. No prior photography experience necessary. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(708, '3', 'ART SINCE 1945', 'ART 366', 0, 'Lecture course covering the principal movements, theories and ideas in visual art since 1945, including painting, sculpture, photography, installation, performance and participatory art.', ''),
(709, '3', '*HISTORY OF DESIGN', 'ART 367', 0, 'A survey of the impact of technology on the visual qualities of graphic, advertising, fashion, architecture, and industrial design from the Victorian Arts and Crafts Movement to the computer age. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(710, '4', 'PRINTMAKING: RELIEF', 'ART 375', 0, 'Studio course in relief printmaking with emphasis on linocut and woodcut; may include other relief processes, i.e. photo polymer plate. Black-and-white and color.', 'Prerequisites: ART 101, 115, 131 and 271.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 101, ART 115, ART 131 and ART 271.'),
(711, '4', 'PRINTMAKING: INTAGLIO', 'ART 376', 0, 'Studio course in intaglio printmaking with emphasis on drypoint, line etching, aquatint, softground and photo process. Black-and-white and possibly color for final project.', 'Prerequisites: ART 101, 115, 131 and 271.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 101, ART 115, ART 131 and ART 271.'),
(712, '4', 'PRINTMAKING: MONOTYPE', 'ART 378', 0, 'Studio course in monotype printmaking with emphasis on drawing/painting with brushes, oil pastels, watercolors, water-based crayons, inking with a lithographic roller and printing with an etching press. Black-and-white and color.', 'Prerequisites: ART 101, 115, 131 and 271.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 101, ART 115, ART 131 and ART 271.'),
(713, '4', 'PRINTMAKING: SCREEN PRINTING', 'ART 379', 0, 'Studio course in screen printing with emphasis on paper stencil, drawing fluid and photo emulsion processes. Students are exposed to a range of techniques and concepts are encouraged to investigate personal motivations while making multiple color prints.', 'Prerequisite: ART 115.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 115.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Graphic Design (779), Applied Visual Arts (859), Visual Arts (878) or Art (880).'),
(714, '4', 'PAINTING II: THE FIGURE', 'ART 381', 0, 'Studio course with emphasis on painting from the live model; understanding the figure in terms of color, form and composition, the figure as symbol, implied narrative and vehicle of expression.', 'Prerequisites: ART 281 and 234.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 281 and ART 234.'),
(715, '4', 'PAINTING II: CONCEPTS', 'ART 382', 0, 'Painting with emphasis on experimentation and an exploratory investigation of mixed media, new media, collage, and assemblage, utilizing either representation or abstraction.', 'Prerequisites: ART 281 and (minimum score of 1 in \'Fine Arts Portfolio Review\' or minimum score of 1 in \'Graphic Design Portfolio Revie\').A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 281.'),
(716, '4', 'PAINTING II: NEW GENRE', 'ART 384', 0, 'Exploration of current directions in painting using traditional and non-traditional concepts and techniques.', 'Prerequisites: ART 281 and (minimum score of 1 in \'Fine Arts Portfolio Review\' or minimum score of 1 in \'Graphic Design Portfolio Revie\').A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 281.'),
(717, '4', 'PAINTING II: ENCAUSTICS', 'ART 385', 0, 'Exploration and application of a variety of traditional and non-traditional techniques using encaustics paint; beeswax and pigment fused to a surface.', 'Prerequisite: ART 281.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 281.'),
(718, '4', 'SCULPTURE II', 'ART 391', 0, 'Intermediate studio course with emphasis in material research and developing greater skills and technical knowledge in sculptural fabrication processes.', 'Prerequisite: ART 291.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 291.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Applied Visual Arts (859), Visual Arts (878), Fine Arts (879) or Art (880).'),
(719, '3', 'SPECIAL TOPICS: Design & Sustainability', 'ART 399', 0, '', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Arts, Media, and Technology (907).Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
