(734, '1 to 16', 'PROJECTS', 'ART 406', 0, '', ''),
(735, '1', 'PRACTICUM STUDENT MEDIA', 'ART 409', 0, 'Practical workshop class offering experiential learning in student media on the Oregon State University campus.', ''),
(736, '1 to 16', 'INTERNSHIP', 'ART 410', 0, 'A one-quarter residency with an appropriate, approved agency or organization where a student may receive practical experience related to the objectives of the Department of Art. The intern observes and produces; the work is supervised and evaluated, both by the agency and the art faculty.', ''),
(737, '3', '^ART IN CONTEXT HISTORICAL AND CRITICAL APPROACHES', 'ART 411', 0, 'Seminar developing writing and research skills in the field of art with interdisciplinary approaches. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisite: minimum score of 1 in \'Fine Arts Portfolio Review\'.'),
(738, '4', 'WOODTURNING WITH SCIENCE II', 'ART 413', 0, 'An in-depth look at how character in wood (figure, spalting, knots, etc.) affects machinability and output in both functional and aesthetic turning. Students will work with a wide range of spalted wood types and figure across numerous species while working on advanced turning forms. Particular emphasis will be placed upon how figure affects grain orientation, how spalting affects density and stability, and how the challenges with character wood can be overcome without specialty tools. Class instruction will be entirely studio based. CROSSLISTED as ART 413/WSE 413.', 'Prerequisites: WSE 210 and 211.A minimum grade of C- is required in WSE 210 and WSE 211.'),
(739, '4', 'NEW MEDIA: INTERACTIVE', 'ART 422', 0, 'An advanced course designing digital experiences with emphasis on innovative navigation, architectural structures, theoretical, and historical issues of new media.', 'Prerequisite: minimum score of 1 in \'Graphic Design Portfolio Revie\'.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(740, '4', 'DRAWING IV', 'ART 431', 0, 'Development of an individual approach to the varied aspects of drawing, emphasis on exploration of traditional and contemporary techniques and styles. Course offered 3 to 5 credits per term.', 'Prerequisites: (minimum score of 1 in \'Fine Arts Portfolio Review\' or minimum score of 1 in \'Graphic Design Portfolio Revie\').'),
(741, '3', '*GENDER, SEXUALITY, AND THE PHOTOGRAPHIC IMAGE', 'ART 432', 0, 'A creative and discussion-based course focusing on ways in which photography can and has addressed issues of gender and sexuality. An introduction to key concepts and intersections in Women\'s, Gender and Sexuality Studies; Queer Studies and photography theory. Create written and photographic responses to artworks, texts, personal experience and pop-culture. CROSSLISTED as ART 432/QS 432/WGSS 432 and ART 532/QS 532/WGSS 532. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Junior or Senior.'),
(742, '4', 'PHOTOGRAPHY III', 'ART 441', 0, 'Using the camera as a tool to sharpen aesthetic and visual perception. Creation of exhibition-quality silver-gelatin prints. Introduction to the view camera. Advanced darkroom techniques. Lec/lab/studio.', 'Prerequisite: ART 341.A minimum grade of D- is required in ART 341.'),
(743, '4', 'DOCUMENTARY PHOTOGRAPHY', 'ART 446', 0, 'Intensive in-depth documentary photography course designed to develop skill in telling stories with pictures. The course requires pitching a photographic project, reading and writing about documentary photography, and producing a sustained photographic essay with a self-selected documentary subject. Expanded documentary mediums and socially concerned photography are also covered. Hybrid Course.', 'Prerequisites: ART 263 and 345.A minimum grade of C is required in ART 263.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 345.'),
(744, '4', 'ADVANCED STUDIO LIGHTING', 'ART 447', 0, 'Practical studio course focusing on the advanced applications of studio and location lighting. Students will use digital cameras in combination with professional strobe and mixed artificial lighting. Real-world location lighting challenges will be mastered: scouting locations, hauling and setting up gear, working with models and products, and learning to work on-location.', 'Prerequisites: ART 263 and 347.A minimum grade of C is required in ART 263 and ART 347.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Studio Art (748)Applied Visual Arts (859)Visual Arts (878)Art (880)Art History (881)Photography (893)'),
(745, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO ARTS ENTREPRENEURSHIP', 'ART 451', 0, 'Survey of the business strategies behind a successful career in the arts. Emphasizes the importance of entrepreneurial thinking, engages students with the fundamentals of the arts \"business\", and explores ways to influence and shape the industry\'s future. CROSSLISTED as ART 451/MUS 451/TA 451. (FA)', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(746, '4', 'ALTERNATIVE PROCESSES IN PHOTOGRAPHY II', 'ART 454', 0, 'Advanced projects using historical photographic processes.', 'Prerequisite: ART 354.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 354.'),
(747, '4', 'THE PHOTOGRAPHIC BOOK II', 'ART 455', 0, 'Practical studio course focusing on advanced practices and techniques in relation to the photographic book. Use appropriated imagery as well as original imagery to complete well-developed book projects. Structure, form, materials, and layout will be discussed as well as content, sequencing, and physical construction. Advanced elements such as application of blanking, slip cases, screen printing, and other construction techniques will be taught. CROSSLISTED as ART 455/GD 455.', 'Prerequisite: ART 355.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 355.'),
(748, '4', 'PORTFOLIO-PHOTOGRAPHY/VIDEO ART', 'ART 456', 0, 'Culmination-level course for the creation of an exhibition-level photographic portfolio or other artistic product using lens-based media. Taught using lectures, critiques, readings, writing and self-reflection.', 'Prerequisites: ART 340, 345 and 347.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 340, ART 345 and ART 347.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Applied Visual Arts (859) or Art (880).'),
(749, '3', 'DIRECTIONS & ISSUES IN CONTEM: DIR & ISS/SITE-SPECIFIC ART', 'ART 462', 0, 'Specialized study of current trends, developments, and critical issues, including the study of new media such as video and photography, as they manifest themselves in the contemporary art world. May be repeated with different topics. Not offered every year.', ''),
(750, '3', 'DIRECTIONS AND ISSUES IN CONTEMPORARY ART', 'ART 462', 0, 'Specialized study of current trends, developments, and critical issues, including the study of new media such as video and photography, as they manifest themselves in the contemporary art world. May be repeated with different topics. Not offered every year.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(751, '3', 'CULTURAL STUDIES OF THE MUSEUM', 'ART 464', 0, 'Overview of the history, visual culture, and cultural significance of the Western museum. Special attention paid to the development of the art museum and artist\'s projects that pertain to museums.', ''),
(752, '4', 'PRINTMAKING STUDIO', 'ART 475', 0, 'Studio workshop in relief, intaglio, lithographic, and silkscreen media on an individual project basis. Course offered 4 credits per term; maximum 20 credits.', 'Prerequisites: ART 101, 115, 131 and 271.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 101, ART 115, ART 131 and ART 271.'),
(753, '4', 'PRINTMAKING: ADVANCED SCREEN PRINTING', 'ART 479', 0, 'Studio course in screen printing with an emphasis on photo emulsion processes. Students are encouraged to integrate these processes with other art-making methods in their creative work.', 'Prerequisite: ART 379.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 379.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Graphic Design (779), Applied Visual Arts (859), Visual Arts (878) or Art (880).'),
(754, '4', 'PAINTING III', 'ART 481', 0, 'Development of individual interests and directions in painting.', 'Prerequisites: ART 382 and 384.A minimum grade of C- is required in ART 382 and ART 384.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Applied Visual Arts (859), Fine Arts (879) or Art (880).'),
