(955, '3', 'BIOMEDICAL ENGINEERING PRINCIPLES', 'BIOE 340', 0, 'Application of engineering concepts (mass and energy conservation, thermodynamics, and transport phenomena) to cellular- and system-level human physiology; design considerations for biomedical interventions and devices.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 231 or Z 331) and (CHE 332 or 332H).A minimum grade of C is required in BI 231, Z 331, CHE 332 and CHE 332H.'),
(956, '3', 'BIOMATERIALS AND BIOINTERFACES', 'BIOE 351', 0, 'Material interactions with human tissue, with emphasis on the role of interfacial chemistry and physics in cell adhesion, infection, blood coagulation and thrombosis. Preparation of functional hydrogels, material coatings, and derivitizations, including immobilized bio-active molecules. Issues surrounding regulation of implants and device failure.', 'Prerequisites: (BB 451* or 451H*) and (CHE 333* or 333H*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in BB 451, BB 451H, CHE 333 and CHE 333H.'),
