(963, '3', 'BIOENGINEERING LABORATORY', 'BIOE 415', 0, 'Laboratory experimentation with unit operations and processes in bioengineering; preparation of technical reports.', 'Prerequisite: CBEE 414.A minimum grade of C is required in CBEE 414.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(964, '3', 'SOCIAL JUSTICE, ETHICS, AND ENGINEERING', 'BIOE 420', 0, 'Examination of difference, power, and discrimination in engineering education and practice. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisite: CBEE 320.A minimum grade of C is required in CBEE 320.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
(965, '3', 'SURFACE ANALYSIS', 'BIOE 445', 0, 'The characterization of molecular, biological, and engineered surfaces by modern surface analytical techniques. Topics include surface sensitive modes of electron spectroscopy, vibrational spectroscopy, and mass spectrometry. Students will interpret surface analytical data and gain access to the surface science literature.', 'Prerequisite: BIOE 351*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in BIOE 351.'),
(966, '3', 'BIOREACTORS', 'BIOE 457', 0, 'Design and analysis of bioreactors using suspension and immobilized microbial cultures.', 'Prerequisites: (BB 451 or 451H) and (CHE 333 or 333H).A minimum grade of C is required in BB 451, BB 451H, CHE 333 and CHE 333H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(967, '3', 'CELL ENGINEERING', 'BIOE 459', 0, 'Application of engineering methods and principles to the study of mammalian cells. Emphasis on mathematical models of cellular processes (e.g., cellular mass transport, protein-ligand interactions, cellular mechanics) and methods for probing the physical characteristics of biological molecules and cells.', 'Prerequisites: (BB 451 or 451H) and (CHE 333 or 333H).A minimum grade of C is required in BB 451, BB 451H, CHE 333 and CHE 333H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(968, '3', 'BIOSEPARATIONS', 'BIOE 462', 0, 'Application of basic mass transfer, reaction kinetics and thermodynamic principles to understanding, selection, and development of strategies for the recovery of products from bioreactors.', 'Prerequisites: (BB 451 or 451H) and (CHE 332 or 332H).A minimum grade of C is required in BB 451, BB 451H, CHE 332 and CHE 332H.'),
(969, '4', 'BIOENGINEERING PROCESS DESIGN', 'BIOE 490', 0, 'Engineering economic analysis. Design of bioprocesess: Development of process flow diagrams, equipment sizing, operation, and safety. Quality control and FDA regulations. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 333 or 333H.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 333 and CHE 333H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(970, '4', 'BIOENGINEERING PRODUCT DESIGN', 'BIOE 491', 0, 'Design of biomedical and biotechnology-based products. Applications of a structured design process, meeting customer needs and regulatory considerations to design.', 'Prerequisite: BIOE 490.A minimum grade of C is required in BIOE 490.'),
(971, '4', 'BIOENGINEERING CAPSTONE DESIGN', 'BIOE 492', 0, 'Culminating experience in bioengineering design of processes and devices. Includes capstone project prototyping, testing and documentation, and constraints in ethics, intellectual property, standards, regulatory, and manufacturing.', 'Prerequisite: BIOE 491.A minimum grade of C is required in BIOE 491.'),
(972, '1 to 16', 'THESIS', 'BIOE 503', 2, 'Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(973, '4', 'MODELING OF PHYSIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS', 'BIOE 512', 2, 'Integration of engineering principles and human physiology in the areas of: transport phenomena in the cardiopulmonary and renal systems, bioelectricity in the nervous system, and mechanics of the musculoskeletal system.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(974, '2', 'DRUG AND MEDICAL DEVICE REGULATIONS IN TECHNOLOGY DEVELOPMENT', 'BIOE 513', 2, 'Overview of the processes by which drugs and devices are regulated by the Food and Drug Administration. Topics include drug and device classifications, approval routes for different classes of drugs and devices, current good manufacturing practices, process validation, and quality assurance and control.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(975, '3', 'SOCIAL JUSTICE, ETHICS, AND ENGINEERING', 'BIOE 520', 2, 'Examination of difference, power, and discrimination in engineering education and practice. Lec/rec.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
(976, '3', 'SURFACE ANALYSIS', 'BIOE 545', 2, 'The characterization of molecular, biological, and engineered surfaces by modern surface analytical techniques. Topics include surface sensitive modes of electron spectroscopy, vibrational spectroscopy, and mass spectrometry. Students will interpret surface analytical data and gain access to the surface science literature.', ''),
