(1181, '1 to 12', 'BUSINESS INTERNSHIP: BUSINESS INTERNSHIP / MECOP', 'BA 410', 0, 'Planned and supervised work experience at selected cooperating business firms. Supplementary training, conference, reports, and appraisals. Graded P/N.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Business college.'),
(1182, '1 to 12', 'BUSINESS INTERNSHIP: BUSINESS INTERNSHIP/MECOP', 'BA 410', 0, 'Planned and supervised work experience at selected cooperating business firms. Supplementary training, conference, reports, and appraisals. Graded P/N.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Business college.'),
(1183, '1', 'FINANCIAL PLANNING I', 'BA 411', 0, 'Part of Blueprint ? a 12 course professional development course series to guide the student from college to career. Third of four courses dedicated to the foundations of professional financial planning so the student can have the tools needed to successfully manage their career pathway.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Business Administration (181)Finance (182)Business Information Systems (183)Management (196)Accountancy (641)Marketing (799)'),
(1184, '1', 'FOURTH YEAR PPL DEVELOPMENT I', 'BA 411', 0, 'BA 411--BA 413 is a series of three one-credit courses taken during a student?s fourth year. These courses, along with the respective 1st, 2nd and 3rd year one-credit courses, are designed to help students navigate college successfully, and develop lifelong skills that are practical, meaningful and useful. These courses revolve around personal, professional and leadership development, and the fourth-year series continues to provide students with career-related skills, and provides students with skills to be successful in life. BA 411 focuses on career placement skills; BA 412 focuses on self-leadership; and BA 413 focuses on work-life balance, financial literacy, and networking.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Business Administration (181)Finance (182)Business Information Systems (183)Management (196)Accountancy (641)Marketing (799)Business Analytics (899)'),
(1185, '1', 'THE DESIGN THINKING CHALLENGE', 'BA 412', 0, 'Part of Blueprint ? a 12 course professional development course series to guide the student from college to career. Topics include basic methodologies of design thinking and integration of design thinking into business processes. Participation in a cross-campus Design Thinking Challenge.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Business Administration (181)Finance (182)Business Information Systems (183)Management (196)Accountancy (641)Marketing (799)Business Analytics (899)'),
(1186, '1', 'FINANCIAL PLANNING II', 'BA 413', 0, 'Part of Blueprint ? a 12 course professional development course series to guide the student from college to career. Fourth of four courses dedicated to the foundations of professional financial planning so the student can have the tools needed to successfully manage their career pathway.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Business Administration (181)Finance (182)Business Information Systems (183)Management (196)Accountancy (641)Marketing (799)Business Analytics (899)'),
(1187, '3', '*ENVIRONMENTAL LAW, SUSTAINABILITY AND BUSINESS', 'BA 432', 0, 'Explores fundamental business, legal, and policy issues raised by environmental law, sustainable business practices, and clean energy policies, and their impact on business and management practices.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(1188, '4', 'TOPICS IN INTERNATIONAL BUSINESS', 'BA 447', 0, 'Analysis of current topics in international business. Topics will vary from term to term.', 'Prerequisites: BA 347 or 347H.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 347 and BA 347H.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1189, '3', 'SUPPLY AND SOURCING MANAGEMENT', 'BA 451', 0, 'Use of operations and supply chain management to make sourcing and supply decisions in international business contexts. Topics include purchasing/procurement procedures and policy, supply organization, specifications, sourcing strategy, supplier evaluation, competitive bidding, and e-procurement. Global contexts and environmentally and socially responsible supply management are emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: BA 357 or 357H.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 357 and BA 357H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.'),
(1190, '3', 'LEAN ENTERPRISE MANAGEMENT AND CAPSTONE', 'BA 454', 0, 'Analyze business cases that address global value creation and production/delivery systems. Complete integrated business projects to identify critical operations and supply chain management issues, apply multidisciplinary knowledge, analyze and evaluate alternative solutions and write and present reports recommending firm strategies. International business and cross-cultural competencies are emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: BA 459 and MGMT 457.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 459 and MGMT 457.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Supply Chain & Logistics Mgmt (694).'),
(1191, '4', 'INNOVATION AND NEW PRODUCT DEVELOPMENT', 'BA 458', 0, 'Strategic management of an organization\'s system and technologies in support of innovation and new product/service development. Application experience with new product/service development process using problem solving skills, information management, and critical thinking.', 'Prerequisites: BA 223, 223H, 390 or 390H.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 223, BA 223H, BA 390 and BA 390H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Management and Marketing (288)Bioenergy (497)Entrepreneurship Bus Majors (624)Family Business (786)Marketing (799)Entrepreneurship (809)Innovation Management (851)'),
(1192, '3', 'SERVICE OPERATIONS MANAGEMENT', 'BA 459', 0, 'Focus on the management of global service operations including designing and managing systems to coordinate global information and material flows within and between firms in a supply chain. Covers planning operations, evaluating system alternatives, designing and researching global supply networks, examining complex adaptive systems and evaluating value stream synchronization.', 'Prerequisites: (BA 375 or 375H) and BA 451.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 375, BA 375H and BA 451.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Supply Chain & Logistics Mgmt (694).'),
(1193, '4', 'VENTURE MANAGEMENT', 'BA 460', 0, 'Entrepreneurial and innovation processes applied to new business start-ups, existing small businesses, and new ventures within larger organizations; new venture planning, project management, and productivity improvement. Cases and projects are used to apply concepts and to develop communication skills.', 'Prerequisites: (BA 260 or 260H) and (BA 351, 352 or 352H) and (BA 223, 223H, 390 or 390H).A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 260, BA 260H, BA 351, BA 352, BA 352H, BA 223, BA 223H, BA 390 and BA 390H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Management (196)Management and Marketing (288)Merchandising Management (416)Business (523)Entrepreneurship Bus Majors (624)Family Business (786)Entrepreneurship (809)Forest Operations Management (823)Innovation Management (851)'),
(1194, '4', 'FAMILY ENTERPRISE GOVERNANCE', 'BA 463', 0, 'Builds on the introductory family business management course to examine the required elements of a successful enterprise, a diversified and multigenerational organization comprised of multiple business lines.', 'Prerequisite: BA 365.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 365.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Agricultural Business Manageme (104)Family Business (783)Agronomy (784)Family Business (786)Agricultural & Food Bus Mgmt (897)'),
(1195, '4', 'NEW VENTURE FINANCING', 'BA 464', 0, 'Explore financial issues facing entrepreneurial business ventures: cash flow and budgets, financial analysis, financial statement forecasting, financial controls, asset management, and understanding the funding options at different points in the business life cycle including SBA loans, angel investment, venture capital, bank loans, and going public.', 'Prerequisites: ((BA 260 or 260H) and (BA 240, 240H, 360, 360H, FIN 340 or 340H)).A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 260, BA 260H, BA 240, BA 240H, BA 360, BA 360H, FIN 340 and FIN 340H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Bioenergy (497)Entrepreneurship Bus Majors (624)Family Business (786)Entrepreneurship (809)Innovation Management (851)'),
(1196, '4', '*SYSTEMS THINKING AND PRACTICE', 'BA 465H', 0, 'Hard and soft systems theories are examined, including methods and techniques for dealing with real-world problems; skills and dialogue techniques to identify mindsets, define problems, and explore alternative pathways for solutions.', 'Enrollment limited to students in a Honors Bachelor of Arts, Honors Bachelor of Fine Arts or Honors Bachelor of Science degrees.'),
(1197, '4', 'INTEGRATIVE STRATEGIC EXPERIENCE', 'BA 466', 0, 'Provides students with an overview of the basic concepts in strategic management. Students learn frameworks and models to understand and analyze a firm\'s external environment and internal resources in an effort to create sustainable competitive advantages. Analysis and critique of conventional conceptions of business ethics. Evaluation of ethical issues involving businesses at firm, national, and international levels.', 'Prerequisites: ((BA 240, 240H, FIN 340, 340H, BA 360 or 360H) and (BA 352 or 352H) and (BA 357 or 357H) and (BA 223, 223H, 390 or 390H)).A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 240, BA 240H, FIN 340, FIN 340H, BA 360, BA 360H, BA 352, BA 352H, BA 357, BA 357H, BA 223, BA 223H, BA 390 and BA 390H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Business Administration (181)Finance (182)Business Information Systems (183)Management (196)Accountancy (641)Marketing (799)'),
(1198, '4', 'NEW VENTURE LABORATORY', 'BA 467', 0, 'Entrepreneurship capstone course. Fully develop a business plan including product specs with prototype, financial analysis, market analysis, marketing plan, management structure and proposed financing.', 'Prerequisites: (BA 357 or 357H) and BA 458.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 357, BA 357H and BA 458.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Entrepreneurship Bus Majors (624) or Entrepreneurship (809).'),
(1199, '3', 'DATA MANAGEMENT', 'BA 474', 0, 'Familiarize students with the major activities involved in collecting and managing data for a data analytics project, including extracting information from relational databases, mapping organizational requirements into a data design, transforming data into information, and exploring basic concepts underlying noSQL data management and analysis methods.', 'Prerequisites: BA 481 or 483.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 481 and BA 483.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Business Analytics (899).'),
(1200, '3', 'DATA EXPLORATION AND VISUALIZATION', 'BA 475', 0, 'Exploring and visualizing data in business analytics projects. We will focus on exploring and wrangling data to discover interesting analysis questions and prepare for other analytics activities. We will pay special attention to data visualization methods and their overall place in data science and business analytics.', 'Prerequisites: BA 481 or 483.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 481 and BA 483.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Business Analytics (899).'),
(1201, '3', 'SUPPLY CHAIN ANALYTICS', 'BA 478', 0, 'Explores modeling methods for design, analysis, execution and integration of supply chains. Introduces students to a variety of modeling and optimization techniques for the analysis of strategic, tactical and operational supply chain problems, including demand forecasting, risk analysis, revenue management, distribution and facility location.', 'Prerequisites: (BA 357 or 357H) and (BA 375 or 375H).A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 357, BA 357H, BA 375 and BA 375H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Supply Chain & Logistics Mgmt (694).'),
(1202, '4', 'BUSINESS TELECOMMUNICATIONS AND NETWORKING', 'BA 479', 0, 'Provide a fundamental understanding of the five-layer Internet model and its effects on the business environment. Planning and managing networks in support of enterprise-wide computing. Assignments involve server hardware and software configurations including DNS/DHCP server configurations, addition of clients to a network, and creating/managing user accounts.', 'Prerequisites: ACTG 378 or 378H.A minimum grade of C- is required in ACTG 378 and ACTG 378H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Business Information Systems (183) or Accounting Information Systems (236).'),
(1203, '4', 'INFORMATION SYSTEMS SECURITY', 'BA 480', 0, 'Course emphasis is on security risk mitigation methods and procedures such as access control, identity management, intrusion prevention and detection, network and physical security, etc. These and other topics will be placed in both the operational and strategic context of the business. The course also addresses several IS governance and IS security frameworks within which the various security concepts, aspects, policies and procedures can be viewed and discussed.', 'Prerequisites: BA 272 and (ACTG 378 or 378H) and BA 479.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 272, ACTG 378, ACTG 378H and BA 479.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Business Information Systems (183) or Accounting Information Systems (236).'),
(1204, '4', 'INTRODUCTION TO BUSINESS ANALYTICS', 'BA 481', 0, 'How organizations can successfully collect, evaluate and apply information for better decision making. Emerging technologies such as transaction processing systems, RFID, weblogs, social networks, website usage, and online communities have the potential to reveal market trends, suppliers\' preferences, and competitors\' next moves. The success of an organization largely depends on its ability to take advantage of those data sets that are already available to it. The class starts with basic IT strategy concepts for the identification of the opportunities for BI solutions, and ends with hands-on experience using Business Intelligence tools to implement such solutions.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Students cannot enroll who have a program in Business Information Systems (183) or Business Analytics (899).'),
(1205, '4', 'INFORMATION SECURITY GOVERNANCE', 'BA 482', 0, 'As a discipline cybersecurity covers software, hardware, networking, systems, individuals, organizations and applicable policies, laws and standards, among others. Given societies? dependence on the security of global infrastructure and the increasing complexity of maintaining the security of those systems, there is a growing need for an interdisciplinary approach to study this topic. This course introduces several well-regarded and well-used IT and IT security governance frameworks which can be used to apply and govern security policies and protocols in organizations. The course also delves into SOC IT auditing.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(1206, '4', 'BUSINESS ANALYTICS', 'BA 483', 0, 'Presents how organizations can successfully \"collect, evaluate and apply information\" for better decision making. Technologies such as transaction processing systems, RFID, weblogs, social networks, website usage, and online communities have the potential to reveal market trends, suppliers\' preferences, and competitors\' next moves. The success of an organization largely depends on its ability to take advantage of those data sets that are already available to it.', 'Prerequisites: BA 371 and 479.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 371 and BA 479.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Business Information Systems (183) or Accounting Information Systems (236).'),
