(1264, '3', 'THERMODYNAMICS', 'CHE 311', 0, 'Entropy, the second law of thermodynamics, equations of state, and thermodynamic network.', 'Prerequisites: (CBEE 212, 212H or 280) and (MTH 256 or 256H).A minimum grade of C is required in CBEE 212, CBEE 212H, CBEE 280, MTH 256 and MTH 256H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1265, '3', 'CHEMICAL ENGINEERING THERMODYNAMICS', 'CHE 312', 0, 'Thermodynamic mixtures, fugacity, phase equilibrium, and chemical reactions equilibrium.', 'Prerequisite: CHE 311.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 311.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1266, '3', 'SAFETY, ENGINEERING ETHICS AND: SAFETY, ENGR ETHICS & PROFESSN', 'CHE 320', 0, 'Introduction to engineering ethics and safety concepts. Topics include professional engineering responsibility, codes of ethics, ethical assessment, conflicts of interest, loyalty and dissent, life-long learning, hazard identification, risk and safety, and process safety management. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CBEE 212, 212H or 280.A minimum grade of C is required in CBEE 212, CBEE 212H and CBEE 280.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1267, '4', 'TRANSPORT PHENOMENA I', 'CHE 331', 0, 'Fundamentals and application of momentum and energy transfer phenomena to fluid flow for the design of industrial chemical engineering equipment.', 'Prerequisites: (MTH 256 or 256H) and (CBEE 212* or 212H*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 256, MTH 256H, CBEE 212 and CBEE 212H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1268, '3', 'TRANSPORT PHENOMENA II', 'CHE 332', 0, 'A unified treatment using control volume and differential analysis of heat transfer, prediction of heat transport properties, and introduction to heat transfer operations.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 311 and (CHE 331 or 331H).A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 311, CHE 331 and CHE 331H.'),
(1269, '3', 'TRANSPORT PHENOMENA III', 'CHE 333', 0, 'A unified treatment using control volume and differential analysis of binary mass transfer, prediction of mass transport properties, and introduction to mass transfer operations. Lec/studio.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 331, 331H, 332 or 332H.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 331, CHE 331H, CHE 332 and CHE 332H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1270, '3', 'TRANSPORT PHENOMENA LABORATORY', 'CHE 334', 0, 'Engineering lab practices and the application of the macroscopic balances of mass, energy, and chemical species; fluid flow, heat and mass transfer experiments by teams for demonstrations of principles established in previous transport phenomena courses.', 'Prerequisites: CBEE 213* and (CHE 333* or 333H*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CBEE 213, CHE 333 and CHE 333H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1271, '3', 'CHEMICAL PROCESS DYNAMICS AND SIMULATION', 'CHE 361', 0, 'Fundamental principles for process dynamic modeling used in the control of process variables such as pressure, temperature, flow rate and chemical composition.', 'Prerequisites: (MTH 256 or 256H) and (CHE 331 or 331H).A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 256, MTH 256H, CHE 331 and CHE 331H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
