(1283, '3', 'CHEMICAL ENGINEERING LABORATORY I', 'CHE 415', 0, 'Theoretical and empirical analysis of several unit operations, use of formal work processes, safety, teamwork, oral and written communication, and personal accountability. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CBEE 414, CHE 411, 443 and 361*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CBEE 414, CHE 411, CHE 443 and CHE 361.'),
(1284, '4', 'INSTRUMENTATION IN CHEMICAL, BIOLOGICAL, AND ENVIRONMENTAL ENGINEERING', 'CHE 417', 0, 'Equips students with a toolbox of instrumental techniques important in chemical, biological, and environmental engineering and the background required to determine the appropriate instrumental technique to address a specific problem. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CH 332 or 335.A minimum grade of C is required in CH 332 and CH 335.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1285, '3', 'CHEMICAL PLANT DESIGN I', 'CHE 431', 0, 'Short-cut techniques and other abbreviated and useful methods for specifying equipment sufficient for the preliminary design of processes and equipment; estimating capital and manufacturing costs based on equipment specifications.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 312, 411 and 443.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 312, CHE 411 and CHE 443.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1286, '3', 'CHEMICAL PLANT DESIGN II', 'CHE 432', 0, 'Transformation of preliminary design to detailed design; introduction to safety, ethical, economical, and environmental considerations in chemical plant design.', 'Prerequisite: CHE 431.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 431.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1287, '4', 'CHEMICAL REACTION ENGINEERING', 'CHE 443', 0, 'Design of chemical reactors for economical processes and waste minimization. Contacting patterns, kinetics and transport rate effects in single phase and catalytic systems.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 312 and (CHE 333 or 333H).A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 312, CHE 333 and CHE 333H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1288, '4', 'THIN FILM MATERIALS PROCESSING', 'CHE 444', 0, 'Solid state devices are based on the patterning of thin films. This lecture and lab course is primarily an introduction to the technology associated with processing thin films. Topics include chemical vapor deposition, physical vapor deposition, plasma etching, and thin-film characterization. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisite: CHE 443*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 443.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1289, '4', 'POLYMER ENGINEERING AND SCIENCE', 'CHE 445', 0, 'Polymer engineering and science with an emphasis on practical applications and recent developments. Topics include polymer synthesis, characterization, mechanical properties, rheology, and processing at a level suitable for most engineering and science majors. Lec/lab/rec.', ''),
(1290, '3', 'CONVENTIONAL AND ALTERNATIVE ENERGY SYSTEMS', 'CHE 450', 0, 'Principles of energy conversion from chemical/mechanical energy to electrical energy including an overview of conventional energy systems and of likely renewable energy systems with a focus on the fundamental physico-chemical and thermodynamic concept for each technology. The economics of energy systems will also be discussed.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 311*, ME 311*, 311H* or CH 440*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 311, ME 311, ME 311H and CH 440.'),
(1291, '3', 'ELECTROCHEMICAL ENERGY SYSTEMS', 'CHE 452', 0, 'Introduces principles and processes of electrochemical energy storage and conversion systems. Topics include fundamentals of electrochemistry and concepts of electrochemical energy storage systems. Examples from batteries, fuel cells, supercapacitors devices will be discussed. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 311 and (CHE 333 or 333H).A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 311, CHE 333 and CHE 333H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1292, '3', 'PROCESS CONTROL', 'CHE 461', 0, 'Principles of PID feedback control based on models of chemical processes; analysis and implementation of proportional, integral and derivative tuning; cascade, feedforward, ratio and deadtime compensation; multivariable control and control system design issues and methods.', 'Prerequisites: (CHE 331 or 331H) and (CHE 332* or 332H*) and CHE 361.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 331, CHE 331H, CHE 332, CHE 332H and CHE 361.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
