(1669, '3', 'PLANE SURVEYING', 'CEM 263', 0, 'Use of field surveying equipment; error analysis; plane surveying methods applied to construction; plane coordinate computations; topographic mapping; and introduction to GPS. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ENGR 211 or 211H.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 211 and ENGR 211H.Students with a term level of Freshman may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Construction Engineering Mgt (338), Pre-Construction Engr Mgt (368) or Architectural Engineering (826).'),
(1670, '4', 'HYDRAULICS', 'CEM 311', 0, 'Pressure and energy concepts of fluids, fluid measurements, flow in pipes and open channels.', 'Prerequisites: ENGR 211 or 211H.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 211 and ENGR 211H.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Construction Engineering Mgt (338) or Architectural Engineering (826).'),
(1671, '3', 'CONSTRUCTION SAFETY', 'CEM 326', 0, 'Training in construction safety with emphasis on hazard identification, avoidance, control, and prevention. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CCE 207 or CEM 407.A minimum grade of C is required in CCE 207 and CEM 407.Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Junior or Senior.'),
(1672, '4', 'CONSTRUCTION ESTIMATING I', 'CEM 341', 0, 'Fundamentals of estimating and bidding construction projects; plan reading, specification interpretation; quantity take-off; types of estimates; estimating and methods of construction for sitework, concrete, and carpentry; estimating subcontracts, estimating job overhead and home office overhead; estimating profit, and computer-aided estimating.', 'Prerequisite: CEM 442.A minimum grade of C is required in CEM 442.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Construction Engineering Mgt (338) or Architectural Engineering (826).'),
(1673, '4', 'CONSTRUCTION ESTIMATING II', 'CEM 342', 0, 'Fundamentals of estimating and bidding construction projects; plan reading, specification interpretation; quantity take-off; types of estimates; estimating and methods of construction for sitework, concrete, and carpentry; estimating subcontracts, estimating job overhead and home office overhead; estimating profit, and computer-aided estimating.', 'Prerequisite: CEM 341.A minimum grade of C is required in CEM 341.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Construction Engineering Mgt (338).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1674, '4', 'CONSTRUCTION PLANNING AND SCHEDULING', 'CEM 343', 0, 'Principles of construction planning, scheduling, and resource optimization; scheduling techniques and calculations; methods for integrating project resources (materials, equipment, personnel, and money) into the schedule.', 'Prerequisite: CEM 342*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CEM 342.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Construction Engineering Mgt (338).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(1675, '4', 'STRUCTURES I', 'CEM 381', 0, 'Introduction to statically determinate analysis and design of steel structures. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: ENGR 213 or 213H.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 213 and ENGR 213H.'),
(1676, '4', 'STRUCTURES II', 'CEM 383', 0, 'Analysis and design of building elements of concrete and timber; detailing and fabrication. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: CCE 321* and CEM 381.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in CCE 321 and CEM 381.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Construction Engineering Mgt (338).'),
