(1696, '1 to 3', 'PROJECTS: Research Apprenticeship', 'COUN 506', 2, '', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1697, '1 to 3', 'PROJECTS: Research Apprenticeship I', 'COUN 506', 2, '', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1698, '3', 'COUNSELING PRE-PRACTICUM', 'COUN 513', 2, 'Designed to develop competencies in basic counseling skills and processes. Self critique, peer critique, and supervisor critique of videotaped interviews with peer clients. A pass requires at least B level work. Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in School Counseling (2980).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1699, '3', 'PRACTICUM IN COUNSELING', 'COUN 514', 2, 'Designed to develop competencies in basic skills, facilitative dimensions, and counseling process. Self-critique, peer-critique, and supervisor-critique of videotaped interview. Written self-critique, oral case presentation and charting skills are learned. A pass requires at least B level work. Graded P/N.', ''),
(1700, '1 to 15', 'COUNSELING INTERNSHIP', 'COUN 515', 2, 'The internship is the culminating field experience of the MS in Counseling program. It is designed to provide the student with an on-site placement in a public or private mental health or school setting that will create the necessary bridge between training and professionalism. Graded P/N.', ''),
(1701, '3', 'DEVELOPMENTAL PERSPECTIVES IN COUNSELING', 'COUN 531', 2, 'A study of affective, behavioral, cognitive, physical, and moral development for human growth and maturation. Theories of personality and learning that affect normal and non-normal development. Relationship of understanding human development to the counseling profession.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1702, '3', 'SOCIAL AND CULTURAL PERSPECTIVES IN COUNSELING', 'COUN 532', 2, 'Social and cultural factors effecting counseling. Includes studies of change, ethnic groups, subcultures, changing roles of women, sexism, urban and rural societies, population patterns, cultural mores, use of leisure time, and differing life patterns.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970).'),
(1703, '3', 'ADDICTIVE BEHAVIOR COUNSELING', 'COUN 533', 2, 'Techniques for addictive behavior assessment and counseling. Specific addictions covered include substance abuse, gambling, and eating disorders.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970) or Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).'),
(1704, '3', 'APPLIED PSYCHOPHARMACOLOGY FOR COUNSELORS', 'COUN 536', 2, 'Acquaints counseling students with the fundamentals of psychotropic drugs. Basics of pharmacology, adverse effects, indications, and drug interactions will be discussed. Boundaries of practice and practical issues of assessment and referral will be covered. The overall aim of the course is to provide information about psychopharmacology to the non-medical mental health care provider so that she or he can be a more informed member of the mental health care team. This course does not purport to prepare the student to be any part of the pharmacological prescriptive process. That is the purview of the medically trained person.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1705, '3', 'THE COUNSELING PROFESSION', 'COUN 541', 2, 'Provides the foundation for becoming a counselor and explores the psychological and philosophical ramifications of the counselor in a changing world. Topics will include values in counseling, ethical and legal issues in counseling, research in counseling, and maintaining a professional identity.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in School Counseling (2980).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1706, '3', 'LEADERSHIP OF SCHOOL COUNSELING PROGRAMS', 'COUN 546', 2, 'Designed to prepare school counselors to lead teams in the development and implementation of comprehensive school counseling programs. Principles of leadership, system change, and advocacy are introduced. State and National Comprehensive School Counseling models are examined.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in School Counseling (2980).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1707, '3', 'SPECIAL EDUCATION ISSUES IN COUNSELING', 'COUN 548', 2, 'Addresses various educational disability categories, the fundamentals of special education law, the special education assessment process, the special education definition of emotional/behavioral disorders, and the counselor\'s role in supporting children with special emotional needs.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970) or School Counseling (2980).'),
(1708, '3', 'FOUNDATIONS OF MENTAL HEALTH COUNSELING', 'COUN 550', 2, 'Addresses the foundations of mental health counseling: (1) historical, philosophical, societal, cultural, economic, and political dimensions of, and current trends in, the mental health movement; (2) roles, functions, preparation standards, credentialing, licensure and professional identity of mental health counselors, (3) policies, laws, legislation, recognition, reimbursement, right-to-practice, and other issues relevant to mental health counseling.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970) or Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).'),
(1709, '3', 'THEORY AND TECHNIQUES OF COUNSELING I', 'COUN 551', 2, 'Basic concepts and facilitative skills of helping relationships. Introduction and overview of counseling theories and their related processes and techniques.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1710, '3', 'THEORY AND TECHNIQUES OF COUNSELING II', 'COUN 552', 2, 'Continued development of the theories and techniques of counseling including identification of the counseling process. Emphasis on personality development and affective, behavioral and cognitive approaches.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1711, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO RESEARCH METHODS IN COUNSELING', 'COUN 562', 2, 'An introductory course for master\'s level students. Explains basic evaluation, quantitative and qualitative research methods in the counseling profession; action research and the fundamental statistical procedures used in the interpretation and use of research studies.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970) or School Counseling (2980).'),
(1712, '3', 'APPRAISAL OF THE INDIVIDUAL', 'COUN 567', 2, 'Development of framework for understanding the individual; methods for data gathering and assessment; individual and group testing; case study approaches; observational, sociometric, and environmental procedures; study of individual differences. Ethnic, cultural, and sex factors are emphasized.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).'),
(1713, '3', 'LIFESTYLE AND CAREER DEVELOPMENT', 'COUN 568', 2, 'Major theoretical approaches to career development; available resources for educational and occupational assessment; procedures to enhance career exploration, planning and placement. Emphasis is on the decision-making process and issues of career counseling with special populations.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970) or School Counseling (2980).'),
(1714, '3', 'GROUP COUNSELING PROCEDURES', 'COUN 571', 2, 'A conceptual and experiential introduction to group dynamics. Group counseling approaches and models; issues of group leadership; styles of leadership and group facilitation skills. Consideration is given to group counseling goals, composition, phases and research.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1715, '3', 'FAMILY COUNSELING', 'COUN 575', 2, 'An overview of the major theoretical approaches to family counseling will be covered. Through the use of readings, demonstrations, and videos the student will become familiar with systems foundations, the history of family counseling, family roles, interaction patterns, and decision-making processes.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1716, '3', 'APPLIED PSYCHOPATHOLOGY AND PSYCHODIAGNOSTICS', 'COUN 577', 2, 'Addresses the principles of diagnosis of psychopathology and the use of current diagnostic tools, including the current edition of the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual (DSM). Includes psychiatric terminology, treatment, current research, cross cultural impact, ethical implications, and goal planning related to mental health processes and case management.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in School Counseling (2980).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1717, '3', 'CRISIS, TRAUMA, AND GRIEF COUNSELING', 'COUN 578', 2, 'The theory and pragmatics of crisis, trauma and grief counseling are addressed.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1718, '3', 'TRAUMA-INFORMED COUNSELING', 'COUN 579', 2, 'Trauma-informed counseling methods for promoting client wellness and resilience are addressed.', 'Prerequisite: COUN 578.A minimum grade of C is required in COUN 578.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1719, '3', 'CROSS-CULTURAL COUNSELING', 'COUN 581', 2, 'Cognitive and experimental study of social and psychological variables influencing the cross-cultural counseling relationship. Social and psychological experiences of selected subcultures. Relevant assessment instruments and current literature, methods and outcome studies.', ''),
(1720, '3', 'MULTICULTURAL COUNSELING II', 'COUN 582', 2, 'Further explores multicultural counseling by studying in-depth the experience of specific student populations and their unique strengths and needs. Students will gain understanding of the specialized school programs and state and national regulations that support a variety of learners as well as the theories and research related to language acquisition to support ELL and bilingual students in the PK-12 system. Students will engage in authentic experiences and assignments to enrich their understanding of sub-populations of students and their families to enhance their cultural responsiveness with those specific groups of learners.', 'Prerequisite: COUN 581.A minimum grade of C is required in COUN 581.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1721, '3', 'INSTRUCTIONAL STRATEGIES FOR SCHOOL COUNSELORS', 'COUN 591', 2, 'Students will gain understanding in research-based classroom teaching practices including classroom planning and evaluation. Students will refine their educational beliefs of classroom practice and gain insight into the administrative structure of public schools as it relates to the teacher and school counselor.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Counseling (2970) or School Counseling (2980).'),
(1722, '3', 'CLASSROOM INSTRUCTION FOR COUNSELORS', 'COUN 592', 2, '75 hours of supervised instruction in a public school setting.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(1723, '3', 'GROUP COUNSELING II', 'COUN 595', 2, 'Group counseling theories and pragmatics for clients with mental and emotional disorders.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).'),
(1724, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO COUNSELOR SUPERVISION', 'COUN 597', 2, 'Introduction to the theory and pragmatics of counselor supervision.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1725, '3', 'COUNSELOR CONSULTATION', 'COUN 598', 2, 'Development of consultation skills as a supervisor and counselor educator. Consultation theory and practice are studied. Students practice consultation skills and receive feedback.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Clinical Mental Health Counsel (2975).Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(1726, '1 to 16', 'RESEARCH', 'COUN 601', 2, '', ''),
