(2099, '4', 'DYNAMICS OF ELECTROMECHANICAL ENERGY CONVERSION', 'ECE 532', 2, 'Generalized machine theory. Techniques for dynamic analysis of electromechanical machines including arbitrary reference frame theory. Lec/lab.', ''),
(2100, '4', 'POWER SYSTEM ANALYSIS', 'ECE 533', 2, 'Fundamentals and control of real and reactive power, steady-state load flow studies, unbalance, stability and transient system analysis.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2101, '3', 'POWER SYSTEM PROTECTION', 'ECE 536', 2, 'Fundamentals of protective relaying. Relay input sources. Generation, transmission, and distribution systems protection. Stability and load shedding.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate or Postbac Degree Seeking level students.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2102, '3', 'SMART GRID', 'ECE 537', 2, 'Fundamentals of smart power grids. Technology advances in transmission and distribution systems, policy drivers, assets and demand management, and smart grid security.', ''),
(2103, '4', 'ELECTRIC AND HYBRID ELECTRIC VEHICLES', 'ECE 538', 2, 'Transportation electrification history, hybrid electric vehicle architecture, powertrain components and their modeling and control, vehicle system dynamics and controls.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2104, '4', 'LINEAR SYSTEMS', 'ECE 550', 2, 'Linear dynamic systems theory and modeling.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
