(2161, '2', 'DESIGN OF COFFEE', 'ENGR 101', 0, 'Roast coffee beans and brew and taste coffee while using engineering design to create the perfect cup of coffee using the least amount of electricity. Lec/rec.', 'Enrollment is limited to INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways level students.'),
(2162, '3', 'ENGINEERING ORIENTATION I', 'ENGR 111', 0, 'Engineering as a profession, historical development, ethics, curricula and engineering careers. Introduction to problem analysis and solution, data collection, accuracy and variability. Lec/rec.', 'INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways level students may not enroll.'),
(2163, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO ENGINEERING COMPUTING', 'ENGR 112', 0, 'Systematic approaches to engineering problem solving using computers. Logical analysis, flow charting, input/output design, introductory computer programming and use of engineering software. Lec/lab/rec.', ''),
(2164, '1', 'SPECIAL TOPICS: ST/ U-SUCCEED', 'ENGR 199', 0, 'Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Pre-Engineering Program college.'),
(2165, '3', 'ELECTRICAL FUNDAMENTALS I', 'ENGR 201', 0, 'Analysis of linear circuits. Circuit laws and theorems. DC responses of circuits. Operational amplifier characteristics and applications. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (MTH 251 or 251H) and (MTH 252 or 252H).A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 251, MTH 251H, MTH 252 and MTH 252H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering, College of Forestry or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
(2166, '3', 'ELECTRICAL FUNDAMENTALS II', 'ENGR 202', 0, 'Sinusoidal steady-state analysis and phasors. Application of circuit analysis to solve single-phase and three-phase circuits including power, mutual inductance, transformers and passive filters. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ENGR 201 or 201H.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 201 and ENGR 201H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering, College of Forestry or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
(2167, '3', 'ELECTRICAL FUNDAMENTALS III', 'ENGR 203', 0, 'Laplace transforms, Fourier series, Bode plots, and their application to circuit analysis.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 201 or 201H) and (ENGR 202 or 202H) and (MTH 256 or 256H).A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 201, ENGR 201H, ENGR 202, ENGR 202H, MTH 256 and MTH 256H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering, College of Forestry or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
(2168, '3', 'STATICS', 'ENGR 211', 0, 'Analysis of forces induced in structures and machines by various types of loading. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: MTH 252 or 252H.A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 252 and MTH 252H.Enrollment limited to students in the following colleges:College of EngineeringCollege of ForestryPre-Engineering ProgramPre-Forestry Program'),
(2169, '3', 'DYNAMICS', 'ENGR 212', 0, 'Kinematics, Newton\'s laws of motion, and work-energy and impulse-momentum relationships applied to engineering systems. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 211 or 211H) and (PH 211 or 211H).A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 211, ENGR 211H, PH 211 and PH 211H.Enrollment limited to students in the following colleges:College of EngineeringCollege of ForestryPre-Engineering ProgramPre-Forestry Program'),
(2170, '3', 'STRENGTH OF MATERIALS', 'ENGR 213', 0, 'Properties of structural materials; analysis of stress and deformation in axially loaded members, circular shafts, and beams, and in statically indeterminate systems containing these components. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: ENGR 211 or 211H.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 211 and ENGR 211H.Enrollment limited to students in the following colleges:College of EngineeringCollege of ForestryPre-Engineering ProgramPre-Forestry Program'),
(2171, '3', 'THE SCIENCE, ENGINEERING AND SOCIAL IMPACT OF NANOTECHNOLOGY', 'ENGR 221', 0, 'Nanotechnology is an emerging engineering field that manipulates atoms and molecules to fabricate new materials and tiny devices. Properties of nanostructured materials, manufacturing methods, characterization methods, and impact on health and safety. Benefits and concerns about nanotechnology will be assessed. Lec/rec. CROSSLISTED as ENG 221/MATS 221.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2172, '3', 'ENGINEERING GRAPHICS AND 3-D MODELING', 'ENGR 248', 0, 'Introduction to graphical communication theory, including freehand sketching techniques, geometric construction, multi-view, pictorial, sectional and auxiliary view representation and dimensioning techniques. Practical application of theoretical concepts using solid modeling software to capture design intent and generate engineering drawings. Lec/Lab.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering, College of Forestry or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
