(2177, '3', 'ENGINEERING ECONOMICS AND PROJECT MANAGEMENT', 'ENGR 391', 0, 'Critical issues in the management of engineering and high-technology projects are discussed. Economic, time, and performance parameters of engineering projects are analyzed from the organizational and resource perspectives. Network optimization and simulation concepts are introduced. Fundamental engineering economics concepts are introduced and applied to planning and managing projects.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering or Pre-Engineering Program colleges.'),
