(2308, '4', 'DRINKING WATER TREATMENT PROCESSES', 'ENVE 421', 0, 'Characterization and treatment of drinking water sources including engineering principles for the selection and design of treatment processes. Lec/rec/lab.', 'Prerequisite: ENVE 322.A minimum grade of C is required in ENVE 322.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2309, '4', 'WASTEWATER TREATMENT PROCESSES', 'ENVE 422', 0, 'Characterization and treatment of municipal and industrial wastewaters including engineering principles for the selection and design of treatment processes. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisite: ENVE 421.A minimum grade of C is required in ENVE 421.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2310, '3', 'AIR POLLUTION CONTROL', 'ENVE 425', 0, 'Study of air pollution sources, transport, and control, including engineering, chemical, meteorological, social, and economic aspects. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: ENVE 321 or 322.A minimum grade of C is required in ENVE 321 and ENVE 322.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2311, '4', 'FATE AND TRANSPORT OF CHEMICALS IN ENVIRONMENTAL SYSTEMS', 'ENVE 431', 0, 'Fundamentals of organic chemistry and engineering principles applied to the movement and fate of xenobiotic compounds. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisites: ((CH 123, 223, 226H or 233) and (CH 440, CHE 331 or 331H) and (ENVE 321 or 322) and ENVE 421).A minimum grade of C is required in CH 123, CH 223, CH 226H, CH 233, CH 440, CHE 331, CHE 331H, ENVE 321, ENVE 322 and ENVE 421.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2312, '3', 'SUSTAINABLE WATER RESOURCES DEVELOPMENT', 'ENVE 456', 0, 'Sustainable water resources engineering principles, assessing the impact of engineering practices. Use of engineering analyses and sustainable principles to design projects and minimize their environmental impact.', 'Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Senior.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Bioengineering (298), Chemical Engineering (303) or Environmental Engineering (311).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(2313, '3', 'BIOREACTORS', 'ENVE 457', 0, 'Design and analysis of bioreactors using suspension and immobilized microbial cultures.', 'Prerequisites: CHE 333 and ENVE 322.A minimum grade of C is required in CHE 333 and ENVE 322.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
