(2324, '4', 'AQUATIC CHEMISTRY: NATURAL AND ENGINEERED SYSTEMS', 'ENVE 532', 2, 'Low temperature thermodynamic and selective kinetic treatments primarily of the inorganic chemistry groups, but also organic ligands and surface active groups, of natural and engineered waters; thermodynamic principles and computational techniques for prediction of equilibrium speciation; comparison of predictions to observations; computer laboratory. Lec/rec.', ''),
(2325, '4', 'PHYSICAL AND CHEMICAL TREATMENT PROCESSES', 'ENVE 535', 2, 'Fundamental principles of physical and chemical processes relevant for the treatment of contaminants in environmental matrices (e.g. water, air and soil).', 'Prerequisite: ENVE 532.A minimum grade of C is required in ENVE 532.'),
