(2530, '1 to 16', 'PROFESSIONAL INTERNSHIP: INTERNSHIP/ URBAN ECOLOGY', 'FW 510', 2, '', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Fisheries Science (1300) or Wildlife Science (1750).'),
(2531, '1 to 3', 'PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: MEETING COMMUNICATIONS', 'FW 514', 2, 'Fisheries and wildlife professionals use meetings of scientists, managers and stakeholders to communicate key findings and develop consensus recommendations for policy. This experiential learning course exposes students to a scientific or management meeting in their chosen field (fisheries, wildlife, ecology, or conservation biology) and gets them to think about how meetings function as well as their content.', ''),
(2532, '3', 'FISHERIES AND WILDLIFE LAW AND POLICY', 'FW 515', 2, 'Provides students with an understanding of the key legal frameworks within which they will work to conserve fish and wildlife resources. Examines federal law and policy relating to allocation and conservation of fish and wildlife resources.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate or Non-Degree / Credential level students.'),
