(2615, '3', '*FOOD SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY IN WESTERN CULTURE', 'FST 260', 0, 'Exploring the sciences and technologies of food processing and preservation within the context of their historical, current, and possible future influences on what we eat, the structure of our society, and our day-to-day lives. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(2616, '2', 'PILOT PLANT EXPERIENCES', 'FST 315', 0, 'Students will be working in one of the FST pilot plants (dairy, vegetables/fruit, brewing, wine making, distilling) and will be assisting with the manufacturing of foods or beverages. Students must have available blocks of time in their schedules to contribute significantly to a production run. Production schedules for each pilot plant will be determined in advance of registration for each term. Not all pilot plants will be available each term. Lab.', ''),
(2617, '3', 'FOOD SAFETY AND SANITATION', 'FST 360', 0, 'Principles, practices, and regulations governing and ensuring the microbiological safety of our food supply through risk assessment, surveillance, and intervention.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 211, 211H, 212, 212H, 213 or 213H) and (CH 121, 221, 221H, 231 or 231H).A minimum grade of D- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, CH 121, CH 221, CH 221H, CH 231 and CH 231H.'),
(2618, '3', 'INDUSTRY PREPARATION/HACCP', 'FST 370', 0, 'Assists students in preparation for internships and employment in the food industry by introducing compliance with food safety regulations, HACCP, and audits.', ''),
(2619, '0', '^COMMUNICATING FOOD & FERM SCI: ^COMM F&FS/BEV & HUMAN HEALTH', 'FST 385', 0, 'This writing intensive course (WIC) will guide students in the investigation and critical evaluation of literature on a topic of current interest in food or fermentation science, and the development of their ability to write concisely and with precision about technical subject matter in this discipline. Lec/rec. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisites: WR 121, FST 360 and MB 302*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in WR 121.A minimum grade of D- is required in FST 360 and MB 302.'),
