(2772, '3', 'FOREST ROAD ENGINEERING', 'FE 415', 0, 'Location, surveying, design, cost estimation, and construction practices for forest roads. Lecture on principles, and laboratory field practice in locating, surveying, designing, and cost estimating.', 'Prerequisite: FE 310.A minimum grade of C- is required in FE 310.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Civil Engineering (306), Forest Engineering (380), Forest - Civil Engineering (381) or Forestry (820).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2773, '4', 'FOREST ROAD SYSTEM MANAGEMENT', 'FE 416', 0, 'Structural characteristics of bridges, load rating, structural design of culverts, aggregate testing and evaluation, environmental assessment of forest road systems, road maintenance cycles and management.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 211 or 211H) and (ENGR 213 or 213H) and FE 316 and 415.A minimum grade of D- is required in ENGR 211, ENGR 211H, ENGR 213 and ENGR 213H.A minimum grade of C- is required in FE 316 and FE 415.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380) or Forest - Civil Engineering (381).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.Students in the Pre-Forestry Program college may not enroll.'),
(2774, '3', 'UNMANNED AIRCRAFT SYSTEM REMOTE SENSING', 'FE 423', 0, 'Unmanned Aircraft System (UAS) Geomatics presents techniques in UAS design and applications for remote sensing measurements of both natural and constructed landscapes.', 'Prerequisites: FE 309, GEOG 480, 481, GEO 444 or 466.A minimum grade of C is required in FE 309, GEOG 480, GEOG 481, GEO 444 and GEO 466.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.'),
(2775, '4', 'WATERSHED PROCESSES', 'FE 430', 0, 'Effects of land use practices on the physical hydrology (interception, infiltration, evapotranspiration, subsurface flow and surface runoff, water yields, and peak flows) of forested watersheds. Surface erosion, mass soil movements, stream temperatures, nutrient levels and effects of management activities upon riparian systems; forest practice rules. Lec/lab.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(2776, '4', 'FOREST WATERSHED MANAGEMENT', 'FE 434', 0, 'Physical hydrology, erosion processes, streams, and riparian areas of forested ecosystems. The material can be widely applied, but is applicable primarily to the humid, temperate rainforests of the Pacific Northwest.', 'Prerequisites: (CH 121, 201 or 231) and (SOIL 205, CSS 305 or 205) and (MTH 241, 251 or 251H).A minimum grade of C is required in CH 121, CH 201, CH 231, SOIL 205, CSS 305, CSS 205, MTH 241, MTH 251 and MTH 251H.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Soil Science (160)Forest Engineering (380)Forest Management (385)Ecological Engineering (450)Environmental Science (542)Forest Operations Management (623)Environmental Sciences (657)Forestry (706)Forestry (820)INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2777, '3', 'FOREST DISTURBANCE HYDROLOGY', 'FE 436', 0, 'Impacts of forest disturbance, including timber harvest, wildfire, insect outbreaks, and low frequency storms and floods on watershed hydrology and streams.', 'Prerequisite: FE 434.A minimum grade of C is required in FE 434.'),
(2778, '4', 'FOREST OPERATIONS ANALYSIS', 'FE 440', 0, 'Identification and measurement of production components in harvesting systems. Methods analysis, productivity improvement and engineering economics. Report writing skills emphasized. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: FE 102 and (FE 370 or 371).A minimum grade of C- is required in FE 102, FE 370 and FE 371.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380), Forest - Civil Engineering (381) or Forestry (820).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.Students in the Pre-Forestry Program college may not enroll.'),
(2779, '4', 'FOREST REMOTE SENSING AND PHOTOGRAMMETRY', 'FE 444', 0, 'Introduction to spectral reflectance, photogrammetry, image analysis, and point clouds. Fundamentals of data acquisition with passive and active sensors installed on airborne and spaceborne platforms. Radar and lidar in forestry. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: FE 257 and (MTH 112, 241, 251, 251H, 252 or 252H) and (PH 201 or 211).A minimum grade of C is required in FE 257, MTH 112, MTH 241, MTH 251, MTH 251H, MTH 252, MTH 252H, PH 201 and PH 211.'),
(2780, '3', '*INTERNATIONAL FORESTRY', 'FE 456', 0, 'An introduction to the biological, physical, and sociological factors that shape the world\'s forests and the activities used to manage those forests. What influence these factors have on forest policies, practices, and outcomes. CROSSLISTED as FE 456/FOR 456. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2781, '4', 'TECHNIQUES FOR FOREST RESOURCE ANALYSIS', 'FE 457', 0, 'Use of linear programming, nonlinear programming, dynamic programming, and simulation to solve complex forest management problems, with emphasis on intertemporal multiple-use scheduling. Forestry transportation problems, multiple-use allocation, and investment analysis. Field trips required. CROSSLISTED as FE 457/FOR 457 and FE 557/FOR 557.', 'Prerequisites: AREC 351 or FOR 330.A minimum grade of C is required in AREC 351 and FOR 330.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Forest Engineering (380)Forest - Civil Engineering (381)Forest Management (385)Forest Operations Management (623)Forestry (706)Forestry (820)INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.Students in the Pre-Forestry Program college may not enroll.'),
(2782, '4', 'FOREST MANAGEMENT PLANNING AND DESIGN I', 'FE 459', 0, 'Integration of environmental, economic, and social aspects of forestry in management planning. Development of strategic and tactical plans using diverse data types and sources. Senior capstone class projects. Lec/lab. CROSSLISTED as FE 459/FOR 459.', 'Prerequisites: FE 457 or FOR 457.A minimum grade of C is required in FE 457 and FOR 457.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380) or Forest - Civil Engineering (381).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Forestry college.'),
(2783, '3', '^FOREST OPERATIONS REGULATIONS AND POLICY ISSUES', 'FE 460', 0, 'Reviews regulations and other policies that affect timber harvesting and other forest practices, particularly policies that address concerns of environment, safety, employment and transportation. Discusses how such rules and other policies evolve, including the role of public perceptions, forestry professionals and other key policy players. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380), Forest - Civil Engineering (381), Forestry (706) or Forestry (820).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.Students in the Pre-Forestry Program college may not enroll.'),
(2784, '4', 'FOREST MANAGEMENT PLANNING AND DESIGN II', 'FE 469', 0, 'A team-based, project-centric course for integrated timber harvest planning. Establish tactical and operational planning goals and constraints, identify feasible harvesting and transportation systems, and design harvest units to meet objectives and constraints. Lec/lab. CROSSLISTED as FE 469/FOR 469.', 'Prerequisites: FE 459 or FOR 459.A minimum grade of C is required in FE 459 and FOR 459.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380), Forest Operations Management (623) or Forestry (820).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2785, '4', 'LOGGING MECHANICS', 'FE 470', 0, 'Relationship of torque, power, and thrust to the operation of cable and ground-based harvesting systems. On-highway and off-highway heavy truck performance.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 211 or 211H) and ENGR 213 and FE 371.A minimum grade of D- is required in ENGR 211, ENGR 211H and ENGR 213.A minimum grade of C- is required in FE 371.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Forest Engineering (380) or Forest - Civil Engineering (381).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.Students in the Pre-Forestry Program college may not enroll.'),
(2786, '3', 'HARVESTING MANAGEMENT', 'FE 471', 0, 'Verification of harvesting assessment plans and operational planning/field layout. Practical logging skills related to harvest planning, operations monitoring, and designing worker training programs. Lec/lab.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380), Forest Operations Management (623) or Forest Operations Management (823).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
