(2831, '3', 'FOREST PATHOLOGY', 'FOR 413', 0, 'Effects of diseases on forest ecosystems. Recognition of important groups, prediction of pathogen responses to environmental changes, and management strategies for protection of forest resources. Field trips. Lec/lab. CROSSLISTED as BOT 413/FOR 413.', 'Prerequisites: BI 204, 212, 212H, 213 or 213H.A minimum grade of C is required in BI 204, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213 and BI 213H.');
INSERT INTO `Course` (`courseId`, `credits`, `courseName`, `courseCode`, `restriction`, `description`, `prerequisites`) VALUES
(2832, '4', 'ADVANCED FOREST SOILS', 'FOR 417', 0, 'Synthesize current information on fundamental properties and processes of forest soils with emphasis on applications to silviculture, soil conservation, and sustainable management of forested ecosystems. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: SOIL 205 and ((CH 231 or 231H) and (CH 261 or 261H) or CH 201) and (MTH 241, 251, 251H, 252 or 252H).A minimum grade of C- is required in SOIL 205, CH 231, CH 231H, CH 261, CH 261H, CH 201, MTH 241, MTH 251, MTH 251H, MTH 252 and MTH 252H.'),
(2833, '3', 'ECONOMICS AND POLICY OF FOREST WILDLAND FIRE', 'FOR 431', 0, 'General overview of the history of fire and the interaction of people with fire on forested landscapes. Forest fire policy history and current issues in the U.S. Basic legal concepts relevant to forest fire policy. An economic framework for understanding spatial externalities, decision-making under certainty, institutional economics, and incentives.', 'Prerequisites: AEC 351, 352, FOR 330 or ECON 352.A minimum grade of C is required in AEC 351, AEC 352, FOR 330 and ECON 352.INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2834, '4', 'WILDLAND FIRE SCIENCE AND MANAGEMENT', 'FOR 436', 0, 'Principles and applications of fire as a natural resource management tool; the role of fire in conservation management, restoration, and preservation of ecosystems. Covers basic techniques and current research used to describe fire behavior and spread, fuels and fuel manipulation, and fire effects on the biota. Focus will be on fire as a natural process in ecosystem dynamics. Lec/lab.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Fisheries and Wildlife Science (133)Forest Management (385)Recreation Resource Management (460)Rangeland Ecology & Management (622)Natural Resources (643)Natural Resources (671)Fisheries & Wildlife Sciences (733)Forestry (820)INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2835, '4', 'SILVICULTURE PRINCIPLES', 'FOR 441', 0, 'Nursery operation, vegetation management, herbivores, fire, seeding and planting techniques. Introduction to principles and techniques involving vegetation control, thinning, fertilizing, and harvesting. Environmental considerations related to forest stand treatments. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (FES 240 or FOR 240) and (FES 141 or 241).A minimum grade of C is required in FES 240, FOR 240, FES 141 and FES 241.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Range/Forestry/Fire Management (156)Forest Engineering (380)Forest Management (385)Recreation Resource Management (460)Terrestrial Ecosystems (529)Natural Resources (643)Natural Resources (671)Forestry (706)INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2836, '4', 'SILVICULTURE REFORESTATION', 'FOR 442', 0, 'Silvicultural principles and practices needed to successfully regenerate forestlands in North America. Topics include artificial and natural regeneration, genetic improvement, seed orchards, forest tree nurseries, site preparation, seedling quality and handling, vegetation management, animal damage protection, early stand management, and ecological and ecophysiological considerations. Emphasis is placed on regeneration methods applied to plantations in western Oregon. Field trips required.', 'Prerequisites: SOIL 205 and (FES 240, 240H or FOR 240).A minimum grade of C is required in SOIL 205, FES 240, FES 240H and FOR 240.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Management (385), Forest Operations Management (623) or Forestry (820).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
(2837, '4', 'SILVICULTURAL PRACTICES', 'FOR 443', 0, 'Manipulation of forest stand structure and dynamics to meet various resource management objectives. Covers key concepts and practices associated with vegetation control, thinning, fertilization, even-aged and uneven-aged regeneration systems including social and environmental considerations associated with treatments. Two-day field trip required. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (FES 240, 240H or FOR 240) and FOR 321.A minimum grade of C is required in FES 240, FES 240H, FOR 240 and FOR 321.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Forest Engineering (380), Forest Management (385), Forest Operations Management (623) or Forestry (820).INTO OSU GE/AE/Pathways or Non-Degree / Credential level students may not enroll.'),
