(3004, '4', 'IGNEOUS PETROLOGY', 'GEO 412', 0, 'Petrogenesis of igneous rocks. Petrographic analysis using polarizing microscopes. Field trip may be required, transportation fee charged. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisite: GEO 315.A minimum grade of D- is required in GEO 315.'),
(3005, '4', 'EARTH MATERIALS III: PETROGRAPHY', 'GEO 415', 0, 'Microscope-based study of minerals and igneous, sedimentary and metamorphic rocks. Representation and interpretation of geological processes based on microscopic observation. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: GEO 201, 310 and 315.A minimum grade of D- is required in GEO 201, GEO 310 and GEO 315.Students with a term level of Freshman may not enroll.'),
(3006, '4', 'GEOCHEMISTRY', 'GEO 430', 0, 'Principles of geochemistry applied to problems of earth science. Field trip(s) may be required; transportation fees charged. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: GEO 315* and ((CH 121 and 122) or ((CH 231 or 231H) and (CH 261 or 261H) and (CH 232 or 232H) and (CH 262 or 262H))).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of D- is required in GEO 315, CH 121, CH 122, CH 231, CH 231H, CH 261, CH 261H, CH 232, CH 232H, CH 262 and CH 262H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(3007, '3', 'ENVIRONMENTAL GEOCHEMISTRY', 'GEO 431', 0, 'An introduction to natural processes at and near the earth\'s surface, as well as an examination of the impact of human activities on the natural environment. Study includes discussion of the sources, transformations, transport, and fate of contaminants. Field trip(s) required; transportation fee charge.', 'Prerequisites: (CH 121, 122 and 123) or ((CH 231 or 231H) and (CH 232 or 232H) and (CH 233 or 233H)).A minimum grade of D- is required in CH 121, CH 122, CH 123, CH 231, CH 231H, CH 232, CH 232H, CH 233 and CH 233H.'),
(3008, '3', 'APPLIED GEOMORPHOLOGY', 'GEO 432', 0, 'Effect of landform processes upon human activity; consequences of resource management strategies on erosional balance within landscape; identification of mitigation of natural hazards; role of geomorphic process studies in environmental planning. Taught as seminar, themes TBA. Field trip(s) may be required; transportation fee charged.', ''),
(3009, '3', 'GEOLOGY OF EARTHQUAKES', 'GEO 461', 0, 'Tectonics of the present day as based on surface geology, geodesy, seismicity, and crustal structure; description of active faults and folds; use of neotectonics in evaluation of earthquake hazard. Field trip(s) may be required; transportation fee charged. Offered alternate years.', 'Prerequisite: GEO 340.A minimum grade of D- is required in GEO 340.'),
(3010, '4', '^GEOPHYSICS AND TECTONICS', 'GEO 463', 0, 'Geophysical observations as constraints on geologic interpretation. Lec/lab. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(3011, '4', 'GLACIAL GEOLOGY', 'GEO 481', 0, 'Mass balance of glaciers, physics of glacial flow, processes of glacial erosion and deposition, glacial meltwater, glacial isostasy and eustasy, and Quaternary stratigraphy. Field trip(s) may be required; transportation fee charged. Lec/lab. Offered alternate years.', ''),
(3012, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO BIOGEOCHEMISTRY', 'GEO 484', 0, 'Interdisciplinary course, applying concepts from chemistry, physics, biology and geology to Earth systems including terrestrial, ocean and freshwater environments; water and energy cycles; carbon, nitrogen, phosphorus and sulfur cycles; biogeochemical cycles through Earth history.', 'Prerequisites: MTH 111 and ((CH 121 and 122) or (CH 231, 261, 232 and 262)).A minimum grade of D- is required in MTH 111, CH 121, CH 122, CH 231, CH 261, CH 232 and CH 262.'),
(3013, '3', 'QUATERNARY PALEOCLIMATOLOGY', 'GEO 486', 0, 'Introduction to geochronology, climate proxies, climate forcing, and climate modeling applied to paleoclimate problems. Emphasis on Quaternary climate history.', 'Prerequisites: (GEO 202 or 203) and (CH 122 or 222 or ((CH 232 or 232H) and (CH 262, 262H or 272))).A minimum grade of D- is required in GEO 202, GEO 203, CH 122, CH 222, CH 232, CH 232H, CH 262, CH 262H and CH 272.'),
(3014, '4', 'HYDROGEOLOGY', 'GEO 487', 0, 'Movement of water through porous media. Darcy\'s Law and groundwater flow equation. Development of groundwater resources. Computer models. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: MTH 252 or 252H.A minimum grade of D- is required in MTH 252 and MTH 252H.'),
(3015, '6', 'ADVANCED FIELD GEOLOGY', 'GEO 495', 0, 'Six-week summer program in central Oregon. Collect field data to make geological maps, cross-sections, columns, and reports. Fee charged.', 'Prerequisites: GEO 295, 315, 340 and 370.A minimum grade of C- is required in GEO 295, GEO 315, GEO 340 and GEO 370.'),
