(3031, '3', 'COASTAL HAZARDS: PROCESSES, RESPONSE, AND ADAPTATION', 'GEO 550', 2, 'Coastal hazards and the associated risks they pose to rapidly expanding coastal communities. Examination of coastal hazards from a trans-disciplinary perspective including the physical processes, the coastal response, and coastal adaptation/management options for dealing with the hazards. Emphasizes probabilistic and other user-inspired approaches for assessing coastal vulnerability to the various hazards.', ''),
