(3048, '4', 'FIRST-YEAR GERMAN', 'GER 111', 0, 'Development of basic writing, reading, listening, and speaking skills; includes cultural component. Designed solely for students with no prior training in German. Native or bilingual speakers of German will not receive credit for GER 111, GER 112, or GER 113. Lec/lab/rec.', ''),
(3049, '4', 'SECOND-YEAR GERMAN', 'GER 211', 0, 'Continuing development of writing, reading, listening, and speaking skills; cultural component. Completion of second-year German or equivalent with a GPA of 2.50 or higher serves as a prerequisite for upper-division courses. Native or bilingual speakers of German will not receive credit for GER 211, GER 212 or GER 213. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisite: GER 113.A minimum grade of D- is required in GER 113.'),
