(3494, '6 to 12', 'HUMAN SERVICES INTERNSHIP', 'HDFS 410', 0, 'Field experience to apply theory and evidence-based practices to individual, family, and community problems in professional settings. Supervision by agency and instructor. Requires 300 hours of work on-site. Seminar includes reflection and constructive criticism processes. Can be taken across 2 consecutive terms (150 hours each) within the same agency. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 107, 209 and 462.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 107 and HDFS 462.A minimum grade of P is required in HDFS 209.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Human Devel and Family Science (447).'),
(3495, '6 to 12', 'HUMAN SERVICES INTERNSHIP: ADV INTERN/ HUMAN SERVICES', 'HDFS 410', 0, 'Field experience to apply theory and evidence-based practices to individual, family, and community problems in professional settings. Supervision by agency and instructor. Requires 300 hours of work on-site. Seminar includes reflection and constructive criticism processes. Can be taken across 2 consecutive terms (150 hours each) within the same agency. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 107, 209 and 462.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 107 and HDFS 462.A minimum grade of P is required in HDFS 209.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Human Services (430) or Gerontology (437).');
