(3497, '12', 'HUMAN SERVICES INTERNSHIP: ADV INTERNSHIP - HS OPTION', 'HDFS 410', 0, 'Field experience to apply theory and evidence-based practices to individual, family, and community problems in professional settings. Supervision by agency and instructor. Requires 300 hours of work on-site. Seminar includes reflection and constructive criticism processes. Can be taken across 2 consecutive terms (150 hours each) within the same agency. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 107, 209 and 462.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 107 and HDFS 462.A minimum grade of P is required in HDFS 209.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(3498, '6 to 12', 'HUMAN SERVICES INTERNSHIP: ADVANCED INTERNSHIP/ HS OPT', 'HDFS 410', 0, 'Field experience to apply theory and evidence-based practices to individual, family, and community problems in professional settings. Supervision by agency and instructor. Requires 300 hours of work on-site. Seminar includes reflection and constructive criticism processes. Can be taken across 2 consecutive terms (150 hours each) within the same agency. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 107, 209 and 462.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 107 and HDFS 462.A minimum grade of P is required in HDFS 209.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(3499, '12', '^CHILD DEVELOPMENT CENTER INTERNSHIP', 'HDFS 430', 0, 'Participation in a research-based model early childhood program focused on student teaching, program development and evaluation, parent education and administration. Placement to be reserved one year in advance. Lec/lab. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisite: HDFS 330.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 330.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(3500, '3', 'FAMILY, SCHOOL, AND COMMUNITY COLLABORATION', 'HDFS 431', 0, 'Focus on family, school, community environments and interactions for children from infancy to adolescence. Resources and skills for enhancing child development across these settings are emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 311 or 313.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 311 and HDFS 313.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(3501, '3', 'CHILDREN AND YOUTH WITH DISABILITIES', 'HDFS 432', 0, 'Developmental, educational, and family issues related to children and youth with disabilities. Highlights a broad range of human exceptionality, including giftedness.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(3502, '3', 'CHILDREN YOUTH W/DISABILITIES: CHILDREN W/SPECIAL NEEDS', 'HDFS 432', 0, 'Developmental, educational, and family issues related to children and youth with disabilities. Highlights a broad range of human exceptionality, including giftedness.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(3503, '10', 'EARLY CHILDHOOD INTERNSHIP', 'HDFS 433', 0, 'Students will complete an internship in a Pre-Kindergarten, Kindergarten or First Grade classroom and will focus on curriculum development, implementation and evaluation, individualizing for diverse student needs and communication with students.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 311, 330 and 331.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 311, HDFS 330 and HDFS 331.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(3504, '4', 'FAMILY VIOLENCE AND NEGLECT', 'HDFS 444', 0, 'Examination of the causes and consequences of family abuse and neglect, including child abuse, domestic violence and elder abuse.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
(3505, '4', '*FAMILIES AND POVERTY', 'HDFS 447', 0, 'Examines families in poverty focusing on causes and consequences of family poverty, including global economic factors, migration patterns, discrimination, and policies and programs for families. Community service required. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(3506, '4', 'FAMILY POLICY', 'HDFS 460', 0, 'Family policies aim to protect, promote, and strengthen families by addressing one or more of the five explicit functions families perform: (a) family formation, (b) partner relationships, (c) economic support, (d) childrearing, and (e) caregiving. This course will explore the relationships between family policies and family functioning using state, federal, and international policy examples. By reviewing theoretical frameworks for conceptualizing family policy, students will assess the consequences policies may have for family well-being.', ''),
(3507, '4', '^PROGRAM DEVELOPMENT AND PROPOSAL WRITING', 'HDFS 461', 0, 'Principles of program development and evaluation applied to the development of a proposal for a human services program; analysis of needs and resources, identification of empirically-based strategies, and assessment. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 360 and 361.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 360 and HDFS 361.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Human Services (430) or Human Dev and Family Sci Gen. (441).'),
(3508, '4', 'PROFESSIONAL HELPING SKILLS', 'HDFS 462', 0, 'Exploration of collaborative, strengths-based methods to resolve individual, family, and community problems. Application of ethical standards to case study, with emphasis on the values of human dignity and social justice. Development of basic helping skills within an empowerment framework.', 'Prerequisites: HDFS 262 and 310.A minimum grade of C- is required in HDFS 262.A minimum grade of P is required in HDFS 310.Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Junior or Senior.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Human Services (430).'),
(3509, '3', 'TOPICS IN HDFS: Compassion Science - Research', 'HDFS 465', 0, 'Topics and issues in human development and family sciences. Examples: children and the law; gender and families; parenting; aging; relationship development across the lifespan.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
