(3540, '3', 'QUANT METH IN FAM/IND DEVELOP: QUANT METHODS:STRUCT EQUAT MOD', 'HDFS 630', 2, 'Advanced quantitative techniques in human development and family studies. Includes longitudinal designs, structural equation modes. Content varies with each offering.', 'Prerequisite: HDFS 532.A minimum grade of B- is required in HDFS 532.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Health & Human Sci or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
