(3727, '4', 'EXERCISE PHYSIOLOGY', 'KIN 324', 0, 'Physiological effects of acute and chronic exercise; factors affecting human performance; exercise training principles.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 233 or 333) and (BI 231 or 331) and (CH 121, 231 or 231H) and (CH 122, 232 or 232H) and (CH 123, 233, 233H or 130).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 233, BI 333, BI 231, BI 331, CH 121, CH 231, CH 231H, CH 122, CH 232, CH 232H, CH 123, CH 233, CH 233H and CH 130.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Nutrition (466), Exercise Physiology (752) or Kinesiology (840).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Science or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
(3728, '3', 'FITNESS ASSESSMENT AND EXERCISE PRESCRIPTION', 'KIN 325', 0, 'Introduction to lab- and field-based physical fitness assessments and the skills needed to design safe and effective exercise programs for apparently healthy adults. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: KIN 324 or EXSS 324.A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 324 and EXSS 324.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Nutrition and Health Sciences (467)Exercise and Sport Science (716)Pre-Therapy and Allied Health (732)Exercise Physiology (752)Kinesiology (840)Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
