(3730, '1', 'PRE-THERAPY/ALLIED HEALTH SEMINAR', 'KIN 343', 0, 'Provides knowledge in professional school preparation and current issues related to the allied health professions.', 'Prerequisites: (KIN 132 or BI 109) and BI 231, 232, 233, 241, 242 and 243.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 132, BI 109, BI 231, BI 232, BI 233, BI 241, BI 242 and BI 243.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Science or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
