(3758, '3', 'APPLIED MUSCLE PHYSIOLOGY', 'KIN 434', 0, 'Skeletal muscle structure, function, and metabolism; applications to muscle fatigue, exercise training, inactivity, and aging.', 'Prerequisites: KIN 324 or EXSS 324.A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 324 and EXSS 324.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Exercise Physiology (752) or Kinesiology (840).'),
