(3760, '4', 'PHYSICAL ACTIVITY, AGING, AND CHRONIC DISEASE', 'KIN 437', 0, 'Addresses the consequences of primary and secondary aging from an individual and public health perspective. Physiological changes associated with aging and chronic disease, functional assessment of older adults, and exercise prescription for older adults with and without chronic exercise will be emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: (KIN 324 or EXSS 324) and (KIN 325 or EXSS 325).A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 324, EXSS 324, KIN 325 and EXSS 325.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(3761, '0', 'ADVANCED ADAPTED PHYSICAL ACTIVITY', 'KIN 444', 0, 'Discuss various disability models and perspectives; reinforce determinants of physical activity; design and implement different physical activity programs and curricula for individuals with disabilities. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (KIN 314 or EXSS 314).A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 314 and EXSS 314.'),
(3762, '4', 'BEHAVIORAL DIMENSIONS OF PHYSICAL ACTIVITY', 'KIN 462', 0, 'Adopting and maintaining an active, healthy lifestyle is difficult. This course explores \"why\" this might be the case and \"how\" to improve upon the situation.', 'Prerequisites: KIN 312 and 370.A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 312 and KIN 370.'),
(3763, '3', 'EXERCISE PHYSIOLOGY LAB METHODS', 'KIN 474', 0, 'Practical experience and projects in exercise physiology lab methods, including measurement of submaximal and maximal oxygen consumption body composition, anaerobic power, and electrocardiography.', 'Prerequisites: (KIN 324 or EXSS 324) and (KIN 325 or EXSS 325).A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 324, EXSS 324, KIN 325 and EXSS 325.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Exercise and Sport Science (716), Exercise Physiology (752) or Kinesiology (840).'),
(3764, '3', '*POWER AND PRIVILEGE IN SPORT', 'KIN 475', 0, 'Issues of power and privilege in sport including race, gender, sexual orientation, disability and aggression and the consequences of long held society norms and stereotypes. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Prerequisites: (KIN 312 or EXSS 312).A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 312 and EXSS 312.'),
(3765, '3', '^ANALYSIS OF CRITICAL ISSUES IN KINESIOLOGY', 'KIN 481', 0, 'Reading and interpreting current research, and using writing as a tool for learning on a critical issue in kinesiology. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Senior.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
(3766, '3', 'TISSUE INJURY AND REPAIR', 'KIN 483', 0, 'Mechanics of tissue injury and the body\'s response and repair following injury of bone, muscle, tendon, ligament, cartilage and nervous system tissue.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 231 or 331) and (BI 241 or 341) and (BI 232 or 332) and (BI 242 or 342) and (BI 233 or 333) and (BI 243 or 343) or ((Z 331, 332, 333, 341, 342 and 343)).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 231, BI 331, BI 241, BI 341, BI 232, BI 332, BI 242, BI 342, BI 233, BI 333, BI 243, BI 343, Z 331, Z 332, Z 333, Z 341, Z 342 and Z 343.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
