(3800, '3', 'PHYSICAL ACTIVITY FOR PERSONS WITH SEVERE DISABILITIES', 'KIN 549', 2, 'Plan, develop and implement appropriate physical activity programs, functional program design, assistive technology, instructional strategies, behavior management practices, and data analysis systems that address the needs for psychomotor performance of persons with low incidence disabilities.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3801, '3', 'HEALTH PROMOTION FOR PEOPLE WITH DISABILITIES', 'KIN 550', 2, 'Discussion will focus on disability and health, theory driving health promotion program development, guidelines for developing a program for individuals with disabilities, and program evaluation.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3802, '4', 'CURRENT TRENDS AND ISSUES IN PHYSICAL EDUCATION', 'KIN 551', 2, 'Current trends and issues in physical education, including curriculum development, professional ethics, instructional practices, and physical activity for the school community.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.'),
(3803, '3', 'INSTRUCTIONAL ANALYSIS TECHNIQUES I', 'KIN 553', 2, 'Introduction to techniques of instructional analysis. Provides in-depth information and training in systematic observation techniques, raw data conversion and inter/intraobserver reliability.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.'),
(3804, '3', 'INSTRUCTIONAL ANALYSIS TECHNIQUES II', 'KIN 554', 2, 'Laboratory/seminar experience to accompany student teaching winter and spring terms. Provides continued application of systematic observation techniques throughout the elementary student teaching experience.', ''),
(3805, '3', 'SKILL ANALYSIS AND ASSESSMENT IN K-12', 'KIN 555', 2, 'Develop proficiency in assessing movement skills, execution of sport techniques, and game play performance. Assessment trends and practices utilized in physical education programs are included.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Health & Human Sci or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
(3806, '3', 'INSTRUCTIONAL SKILLS I', 'KIN 556', 2, 'Skills of planning, implementing, and evaluating programs of instruction in physical education, grades K-12.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3807, '2', 'INSTRUCTIONAL SKILLS II', 'KIN 557', 2, 'Applying and refining skills of planning, implementing, and evaluating programs of instruction in physical education, grades K-12.', ''),
(3808, '3', 'PHYS ED CURRIC DESIGN & ORGAN: PHY ED CURRIC DESIGN & ORGANIZ', 'KIN 558', 2, 'Curricular programs and variations from kindergarten through grade 12, administrative policies and practices.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.'),
(3809, '1', 'THE PHYSICAL EDUCATOR AS A PROFESSIONAL', 'KIN 559', 2, 'Transitioning to teaching, developing a portfolio, certification, obtaining a position, teacher burnout, professionalism, problems of first-year teachers, developing patterns of behavior that lead to a successful career.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3810, '3', 'PSYCHOSOCIAL FACTORS IN PHYSICAL ACTIVITY', 'KIN 561', 2, 'A social psychological approach to understanding the role of social interactions and contextual factors in explaining human behavior in sport and exercise settings.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3811, '3', 'PROGRAM CAPSTONE AND SYNTHESIS', 'KIN 564', 2, 'Capstone course in which teacher candidates will review and update their teaching philosophy; showcase their Physical Education master?s portfolio; and develop a plan for professional development.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 510.A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 510.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3812, '3', 'EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT OF SPORTS TRAUMA', 'KIN 565', 2, 'Knowledge and skills related to the specialized care required for serious and/or life-threatening acute athletic related injuries and illnesses. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 511.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 511.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(3813, '4', 'GENERAL MEDICAL ASSESSMENT', 'KIN 566', 2, 'Prevention, evaluation, diagnosis, and management of general medical conditions commonly encountered by the athletic trainer.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 565.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 565.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).'),
(3814, '3', 'PHARMACOLOGY IN ATHLETIC TRAINING', 'KIN 567', 2, 'Pharmacology in sports medicine, topics including, but not limited to, the mechanisms and actions of drugs commonly administered and prescribed in sports medicine environments.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 566.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 566.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).'),
(3815, '3', 'ATHLETIC TRAINING PROGRAM MANAGEMENT', 'KIN 568', 2, 'Administrative aspects of athletic training program management. Including principles of risk management, strategic and operational planning, medical-legal aspects of athletic healthcare, confidentiality and documentation of patient health information, insurance and third-party reimbursement, personnel issues, and current professional issues.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 522.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 522.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
(3816, '3', 'EVIDENCE-BASED PRACTICE', 'KIN 569', 2, 'Principles and skills underlying the utilization of evidence to enhance clinical practice decision-making. Includes the development of clinical questions, review and appraisal of relevant literature, and utilization of patient-centered outcome measures.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 521.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 521.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Health & Human Sci or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
(3817, '3', 'RESEARCH IN HUMAN MOVEMENT', 'KIN 575', 2, 'Investigation and evaluation of research methods applicable to human movement study and professional physical education', ''),
(3818, '3', 'PHYSIOLOGY AND MANAGEMENT OF MUSCULOSKELETAL INJURIES', 'KIN 584', 2, 'Mechanics of musculoskeletal tissue injuries; physiologic response and repair processes of various tissues; and effects of physical agents commonly used by athletic trainers in the care and treatment of musculoskeletal injuries.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 511.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 511.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).'),
(3819, '4', 'UPPER EXTREMITY THERAPEUTIC EXERCISE', 'KIN 585', 2, 'Principles and techniques of therapeutic exercise and manual therapy for the upper extremity, cervical spine, and thoracic spine. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 586.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 586.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).'),
(3820, '4', 'LOWER EXTREMITY THERAPEUTIC EXERCISE', 'KIN 586', 2, 'Principles and techniques of therapeutic exercise and manual therapy with a focus on the lower extremity, lumbar spine and ribs.', 'Prerequisite: KIN 584.A minimum grade of C is required in KIN 584.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Athletic Training (2440).'),
