(4139, '4', 'THERMODYNAMICS', 'ME 312', 0, 'Exergy destruction, machine and cycle processes, law of corresponding states, non-reactive gas mixtures, reactive mixtures, thermodynamics of compressible fluid flow. CROSSLISTED as ME 312/NSE 312.', 'Prerequisites: (MTH 256 or 256H) and (ME 311, 311H, NSE 311, 311H, NE 311 or 311H).A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 256, MTH 256H, ME 311, ME 311H, NSE 311, NSE 311H, NE 311 and NE 311H.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Engineering Physics (312), Manufacturing Engineering (317) or Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4140, '3', 'MECHANICS OF MATERIALS', 'ME 316', 0, 'Determination of stresses, deflections, and stability of deformable bodies with an introduction to finite element analysis.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 213 or 213H) and (MTH 256 or 256H).A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 213, ENGR 213H, MTH 256 and MTH 256H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Mechanical Engineering (321) or Product Development (833).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4141, '4', 'INTERMEDIATE DYNAMICS', 'ME 317', 0, 'Continuation of the study of kinematics and kinetics of particles and rigid bodies, with applications to mechanical systems of current interest to engineers.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 212 or 212H) and (MTH 256 or 256H).A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 212, ENGR 212H, MTH 256 and MTH 256H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Mechanical Engineering (321) or Product Development (833).'),
(4142, '4', 'INTRODUCTORY FLUID MECHANICS', 'ME 331', 0, 'Introduces the concepts and applications of fluid mechanics and dimensional analysis with an emphasis on fluid behavior, internal  and external flows, analysis of engineering applications of incompressible pipe systems, and external aerodynamics. CROSSLISTED as ME 331/NSE 331.', 'Prerequisites: ((MTH 254 or 254H) and (MTH 256 or 256H) and (ENGR 212 or 212H) and (ENGR 311, ME 311, 311H, NSE 311, 311H, NE 311 or 311H)).A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 254, MTH 254H, MTH 256, MTH 256H, ENGR 212, ENGR 212H, ENGR 311, ME 311, ME 311H, NSE 311, NSE 311H, NE 311 and NE 311H.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Energy Systems Engineering (293).Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(4143, '4', 'HEAT TRANSFER', 'ME 332', 0, 'A treatment of conductive, convective and radiative energy transfer using control volume and differential analysis and prediction of transport properties. CROSSLISTED as ME 332/NSE 332.', 'Prerequisites: ((MTH 256 or 256H) and (ENGR 212 or 212H) and (ME 311, 311H, NE 311 or 311H) and (ME 331, 331H, NSE 331, 331H, NE 331 or 331H)).A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 256, MTH 256H, ENGR 212, ENGR 212H, ME 311, ME 311H, NE 311, NE 311H, ME 331, ME 331H, NSE 331, NSE 331H, NE 331 and NE 331H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Mechanical Engineering (321) or Product Development (833).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4144, '4', 'MECHANICAL ENGINEERING METHODS', 'ME 373', 0, 'Analytical and numerical methods for solving representative mechanical engineering problems. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: (ENGR 112 or 112H) and (MTH 256 or 256H) and MTH 341.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 112, ENGR 112H, MTH 256, MTH 256H and MTH 341.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4145, '4', 'INTRODUCTION TO DESIGN', 'ME 382', 0, 'Organization, planning, economics, and the use of creativity and optimization in solving mechanical design problems. Case studies and/or industrial design problems. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ENGR 248, ME 250*, ENGR 212 and 213.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in ENGR 248, ME 250, ENGR 212 and ENGR 213.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Manufacturing Engineering (317) or Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4146, '4', 'MECHANICAL COMPONENT DESIGN', 'ME 383', 0, 'Failure analysis and design of machine components. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ME 316 and 250* and (ENGR 212 or 212H) and ENGR 213.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 316, ME 250, ENGR 212, ENGR 212H and ENGR 213.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Mechanical Engineering (321) or Product Development (833).'),
(4147, '0', 'MECHANICAL COMPONENT DESIGN: MECHANICAL COMPONENT  DESIGN', 'ME 383', 0, 'Failure analysis and design of machine components. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ME 316 and 250* and (ENGR 212 or 212H) and ENGR 213.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 316, ME 250, ENGR 212, ENGR 212H and ENGR 213.'),
