(4158, '4', 'AEROSPACE APPLICATIONS IN MECHANICAL ENGINEERING', 'ME 411', 0, 'Provides students with the fundamentals of mechanical engineering applications to aerospace. Topics covered include an overview of modern aircraft and spacecraft analysis, with an emphasis on performance, stability, structures, materials, FAA and FAR standards and current professional practices in the conceptual design of aerospace vehicles. Student projects will integrate course topics.', 'Prerequisites: (ME 316 and (ME 317 or 317H) and (ME 331 or 331H) and (ME 373 or 373H)).A minimum grade of C is required in ME 316, ME 317, ME 317H, ME 331, ME 331H, ME 373 and ME 373H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4159, '4', 'DESIGN OF MECHANISMS', 'ME 412', 0, 'Analysis and study of the function, classification, position, velocity, and acceleration of multi-element mechanical linkages and mechanisms. Synthesis of mechanisms for specified multiple point paths, quick return, dwell, and straight-line motion. The lecture will instruct students in the kinematic analysis and synthesis of mechanisms through the use of theory and software packages. The laboratory will familiarize students with a modern mechanism design and animation software package. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (ME 317 or 317H) and ME 383.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 317, ME 317H and ME 383.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4160, '4', 'COMPUTER-AIDED DESIGN AND MANUFACTURING', 'ME 413', 0, 'Introduces students to the use of computers in several extended areas of product design and manufacturing. These areas include product data management in a sustaining engineering environment; computer-aided manufacturing (CAM) and computer numerical control (CNC) operations and technology; the use of programmable logic controllers (PLCs) for industrial control systems; and the use of simulation software for virtual prototyping for Design/Manufacturing/Validation. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ME 382, 382H or IE 366.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 382, ME 382H and IE 366.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Manufacturing Engineering (317), Mechanical Engineering (321) or Industrial Engineering (323).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4161, '4', 'MECHANICAL VIBRATIONS', 'ME 422', 0, 'Dynamic response of single and multiple degree-of-freedom systems.', 'Prerequisites: ME 317 or 317H.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 317 and ME 317H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4162, '3', 'FINITE ELEMENT MODELING OF MECHANICAL ENGINEERING SYSTEMS', 'ME 424', 0, 'Application of modern finite element code in the analysis of complex mechanical engineering systems. Extensive use of engineering workstations. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ME 420 or 520.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 420 and ME 520.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4163, '4', 'SYSTEMS DYNAMICS AND CONTROL', 'ME 430', 0, 'Modeling and analysis of linear continuous systems in time and frequency domains. Fundamentals of single-input-single-output control system design. CROSSLISTED as ECE 451/ME 430.', 'Prerequisites: (ME 317 or 317H or (ECE 351 and 352 and (ENGR 212 or 212H))).A minimum grade of C is required in ME 317, ME 317H, ECE 351, ECE 352, ENGR 212 and ENGR 212H.Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore or Junior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4164, '4', 'THERMAL SYSTEMS DESIGN AND ANALYSIS', 'ME 444', 0, 'Integration of the concepts, laws, and methodologies from fluid mechanics, heat transfer, and thermodynamics, into a set of practical tools for thermal energy systems design and analysis.', 'Prerequisites: (ME 332, 332H, NSE 332 or 332H) and (ME 312*, 312H*, NSE 312* or 312H*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 332, ME 332H, NSE 332, NSE 332H, ME 312, ME 312H, NSE 312 and NSE 312H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Mechanical Engineering (321).'),
(4165, '4', 'INTRODUCTION TO COMBUSTION', 'ME 445', 0, 'Study of combustion science based on the background of chemistry, thermodynamics, fluid mechanics, heat and mass transfer. Stoichiometry, energetics of chemical reactions, flame temperature, equilibrium product analyses, chemical kinetics, and chain reactions.', 'Prerequisites: (ME 312 or 312H) and (ME 332 or 332H).A minimum grade of C is required in ME 312, ME 312H, ME 332 and ME 332H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4166, '4', 'APPLIED HEAT TRANSFER', 'ME 450', 0, 'An intermediate heat transfer course seeking to lay a foundation for determining the heating and cooling characteristics with a variety of modern and classical processes. Included is design of multi-component heat transfer systems. Lecture, 110 minutes twice per week.', 'Prerequisites: ME 332 or 332H.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 332 and ME 332H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Mechanical Engineering (321).Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.');
