(4248, '1 to 10', 'OCCUPATIONAL INTERNSHIP', 'MB 410', 0, 'Supervised work experience at selected cooperating institutions, agencies, laboratories, clinics or companies. Maximum of 10 credits allowed but no more than 3 credits may be used to satisfy microbiology major requirement of 36 credits. Graded P/N.', ''),
(4249, '3', 'IMMUNOLOGY', 'MB 416', 0, 'Basic theory and applications of immunochemistry, immunogenetics, and cellular immunology. Examination of immunologically related diseases.', 'Prerequisites: BB 450 or 490.A minimum grade of D- is required in BB 450 and BB 490.'),
(4250, '2', 'IMMUNOLOGY LABORATORY', 'MB 417', 0, 'Laboratory on the applications of current immunological techniques.', 'Prerequisites: (MB 303 or 303H) and MB 416*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 303, MB 303H and MB 416.'),
(4251, '3', 'MICROBIAL GENOMES, BIOGEOCHEMISTRY, AND DIVERSITY', 'MB 420', 0, 'A survey of microbial diversity from the earliest lifeforms to the modern role of bacteria and archaea in global biogeochemical cycles. Topics covered include molecular evolution, microbial genomics, biochemical diversity, and metabolic pathways that adapt cells to extreme environments. Particular emphasis is placed on marine systems, from photosynthesis in surface waters to life in the ocean crust.', 'Prerequisite: BB 451.A minimum grade of D- is required in BB 451.'),
(4252, '2', 'AQUATIC MICROBIOLOGY LABORATORY', 'MB 422', 0, 'Laboratory analyzing field samples from freshwater and marine systems to examine patterns of microbiological communities.', 'Prerequisites: MB 303 and 314.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 303 and MB 314.'),
(4253, '3', 'BACTERIAL PATHOGENESIS', 'MB 430', 0, 'Bacteria pathogenic for humans, emphasizing the structural, physiological and genetic mechanisms of pathogenesis. Role of the immune system in pathogenesis and protection.', 'Prerequisites: MB 302 and 310 and (BB 451 or 491).A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 302, MB 310, BB 451 and BB 491.'),
(4254, '3', 'VIROLOGY', 'MB 434', 0, 'Properties of viruses, their biology and pathogenesis. Emphasis on viruses causing human disease.', 'Prerequisites: ((BB 450 or 450H) and (BB 451 or 451H)) or (BB 490, 491 and 492).A minimum grade of D- is required in BB 450, BB 450H, BB 451, BB 451H, BB 490, BB 491 and BB 492.'),
(4255, '2', 'PATHOGENIC MICROBES LABORATORY', 'MB 435', 0, 'Laboratory experiments to illustrate concepts presented in MB 430 and/or MB 434, focusing on pathogenic microorganisms.', 'Prerequisites: (MB 303 or 303H) and MB 302 and (MB 430* or 434*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 303, MB 303H, MB 302, MB 430 and MB 434.'),
(4256, '3', 'THE HUMAN MICROBIOME', 'MB 436', 0, 'Examines the biodiversity, function, and medical importance of the communities of microorganisms that inhabit the human body. A diverse array of topics will be discussed, including how the human microbiome is studied, case studies of specific aspects of the human microbiome, and emerging theories of how the microbiome influences human health.', 'Prerequisites: BI 314, BB 314, BI 314H or MB 302.A minimum grade of D- is required in BI 314, BB 314, BI 314H and MB 302.'),
(4257, '3', 'FOOD MICROBIOLOGY', 'MB 440', 0, 'Role of microorganisms in food spoilage, infection, and intoxication; also basic principles in contamination control and germicidal treatment during processing, preparing, and distributing food for consumption.', 'Prerequisite: MB 302.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 302.'),
(4258, '2', 'FOOD MICROBIOLOGY LABORATORY', 'MB 441', 0, 'Laboratory techniques to accompany MB 440/MB 540.', 'Prerequisites: (MB 303 or 303H) and MB 440*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 303, MB 303H and MB 440.'),
(4259, '3', 'MICROBIAL ECOLOGY', 'MB 448', 0, 'A comparison of soil sediments and freshwater as microbial habitats. Discussion of the role of microorganisms in nutrient cycles, effects of microbial activity on plant and animal life.', 'Prerequisite: MB 302.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 302.'),
(4260, '3', 'MICROBIAL GENETICS AND BIOTECHNOLOGY', 'MB 456', 0, 'General biology of natural, genetically engineered, and composite plasmids. Major topics include extrachromosomal DNA replication, plasmid transmission, insertion elements, transposons, gene expression, and recombinant DNA vectors. Biotechnological applications and molecular genetic tools are emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: MB 302 and (BB 450 or 490) and (BB 451 or 491) and (MB 310 or BB 492).A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 302, BB 450, BB 490, BB 451, BB 491, MB 310 and BB 492.'),
(4261, '3', 'FERMENTATION MICROBIOLOGY', 'MB 479', 0, 'An introduction to industrial microbiology with a focus on the physiology of fermentation and use of microorganisms for the production of food ingredients, fermented foods, and beverages. FST students need to take BB 350 and MB students need to take BB 450 for their respective majors. CROSSLISTED as FST 479/MB 479 and FST 579/MB 579.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 212 or 212H) and CH 331 and 332 and (BB 350 or 450) and MB 302.A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 212, BI 212H, CH 331 and CH 332.A minimum grade of D- is required in BB 350, BB 450 and MB 302.'),
(4262, '3', 'GENERAL PARASITOLOGY', 'MB 480', 0, 'Introduction to parasitology. The course emphasizes medical parasitology, but will cover a broad overview of parasitology, covering important groups and host/parasite relationships among all taxa from invertebrates to vertebrates, including mammals.', ''),
(4263, '2', 'MICROBIOLOGY CAPSTONE EXPERIENCE', 'MB 490', 0, 'Capstone experience for microbiology students to practice professional skills necessary to sustain a career in science. Students will work in teams to analyze research data and communicate this analysis, in addition to explore career opportunities and learn how to successfully compete for jobs. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisite: MB 302.A minimum grade of D- is required in MB 302.Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Junior or Senior.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Microbiology (570).'),
