(4722, '2', 'NUCLEAR RULES AND REGULATIONS', 'NSE 415', 0, 'An introduction to the key nuclear regulatory agencies; major nuclear legislation; current radiation protection standards and organizations responsible for their implementation. Offered alternate years.', 'Prerequisite: NSE 236.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 236.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4723, '4', 'RADIATION SHIELDING AND EXTERNAL DOSIMETRY', 'NSE 435', 0, 'Theoretical principles of shielding for neutron and gamma radiation; external dosimetry fundamentals for neutrons, photons, and charged particles; applications to problems of practical interest; analytical, numerical, and computer solutions emphasized.', 'Prerequisites: (NSE 234, NE 234 or RHP 234) and (NSE 235, NE 235 or RHP 235) and (NSE 481, NE 481 or RHP 481).A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 234, NE 234, RHP 234, NSE 235, NE 235, RHP 235, NSE 481, NE 481 and RHP 481.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4724, '4', 'NUCLEAR FUEL CYCLE AND WASTE MANAGEMENT', 'NSE 440', 0, 'Mining, milling, conversion, enrichment, fuel fabrication, reprocessing, and waste management of nuclear fuel, including disposal of low- and high-level radioactive waste.', 'Prerequisites: NSE 235, NE 235 or RHP 235.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 235, NE 235 and RHP 235.'),
(4725, '3', 'NEUTRONIC ANALYSIS I', 'NSE 451', 0, 'Physical models of neutronic systems; nuclear physics; steady state and transient neutronic system behavior; introductory neutron transport theory, one speed diffusion theory; numerical methods; fast and thermal spectrum calculations; multigroup methods; transmutation and burnup; reactor fuel management; reactivity control; perturbation theory; neutronic laboratory sessions.', 'Prerequisites: (MTH 256 or 256H) and (NSE 235, NE 235 or RHP 235) and (NSE 333, NE 333 or RHP 333).A minimum grade of C is required in MTH 256, MTH 256H, NSE 235, NE 235, RHP 235, NSE 333, NE 333 and RHP 333.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4726, '3', 'NEUTRONIC ANALYSIS II: NEUTRONIC ANALY & LAB II', 'NSE 452', 0, 'Physical models of neutronic systems; nuclear physics; steady state and transient neutronic system behavior; introductory neutron transport theory, one speed diffusion theory; numerical methods; fast and thermal spectrum calculations; multigroup methods; transmutation and burnup; reactor fuel management; reactivity control; perturbation theory; neutronic laboratory sessions. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: NSE 451 or NE 451.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 451 and NE 451.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4727, '3', 'REACTOR OPERATOR TRAINING I', 'NSE 455', 0, 'The Oregon State University TRIGA reactor Operator Training I class is one of a two-course series. Students interested in participating in this course are expected to enroll in both the NSE 455/NSE 555 and NSE 456/NSE 556 classes taught during spring and summer terms. Students successfully completing the NSE 455/NSE 555 and NSE 456/NSE 556 series will culminate their course work with the opportunity to take a certification test proctored by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission.', 'Prerequisites: (NSE 236, NE 236 or RHP 236) and (MTH 256 or 256H).A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 236, NE 236, RHP 236, MTH 256 and MTH 256H.'),
(4728, '2', 'NUCLEAR REACTOR LABORATORY', 'NSE 457', 0, 'Experimental investigation of the principles of nuclear reactor operation. Use of the OSU TRIGA Reactor and other laboratory facilities. Preparation and presentation of laboratory reports. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (NSE 451, NE 451, NSE 551 or NE 551) and (NSE 452, NE 452, NSE 552 or NE 552).A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 451, NE 451, NSE 551, NE 551, NSE 452, NE 452, NSE 552 and NE 552.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4729, '4', 'NUCLEAR REACTOR THERMAL HYDRAULICS', 'NSE 467', 0, 'Hydrodynamics and conductive, convective and radiative heat transfer in nuclear reactor systems. Core heat removal design; critical heat flux, hot spot factors, single- and two-phase flow behavior. Advanced thermal hydraulic computer codes.', 'Prerequisites: ME 332, 332H, NSE 332, 332H, NE 332 or 332H.A minimum grade of C is required in ME 332, ME 332H, NSE 332, NSE 332H, NE 332 and NE 332H.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4730, '3', 'NUCLEAR REACTOR SYSTEMS ANALYSIS', 'NSE 473', 0, 'Analysis of nuclear light water reactor (pressurized water reactor and boiling water reactor) design and operation, including the nuclear steam supply system, engineered safety features and balance of plant systems; regulatory design requirements; industry standards; plant engineering and instrumentation drawings. Advanced reactor system designs.', 'Prerequisites: NSE 452 or NE 452.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 452 and NE 452.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4731, '4', '^NUCLEAR SYSTEMS DESIGN I', 'NSE 474', 0, 'Part I of a two-part series aimed at developing the student\'s ability to utilize fundamental nuclear and radiation protection skills to transform concepts into practical designs. Design projects involve the integration of neutronics, thermal hydraulics, safety and risk analysis, power production, materials, radiation protection, economic optimization, statistics and other skills. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisite: NSE 481.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 481.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4732, '4', '^NUCLEAR SYSTEMS DESIGN II', 'NSE 475', 0, 'Part II of a two-part series aimed at developing the student\'s ability to utilize fundamental nuclear and radiation protection skills to transform concepts into practical designs. Design projects involve the integration of neutronics, thermal hydraulics, safety and risk analysis, power production, materials, radiation protection, economic optimization, statistics and other skills. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisites: (NSE 452 or NE 452) and (NSE 474, NE 474 or RHP 474).A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 452, NE 452, NSE 474, NE 474 and RHP 474.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4733, '4', 'RADIATION PROTECTION', 'NSE 481', 0, 'Fundamental principles and theory of radiation protection; regulatory agencies, dose units; source of radiation; biological effects and risk; dose limits; applications of external and internal dosimetry; shielding and atmospheric dispersion.', 'Prerequisites: NSE 235, NE 235 or RHP 235.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 235, NE 235 and RHP 235.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4734, '3', 'RADIATION BIOLOGY', 'NSE 483', 0, 'Biological effects of ionizing radiation at the molecular, cellular, and organismal levels with emphasis on vertebrates; both acute and chronic radiation effects are considered.', 'Prerequisites: NSE 481, RHP 481 or MP 481.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 481, RHP 481 and MP 481.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
(4735, '3', 'RADIOECOLOGY', 'NSE 488', 0, 'Radionuclides in the environment: their measurement and identification, uptake and transfer through food chains. Effect of radiation on natural populations of plants and animals.', 'Prerequisites: NSE 481, RHP 481 or NE 481.A minimum grade of C is required in NSE 481, RHP 481 and NE 481.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Engineering college.'),
