(4793, '3', '*FOOD IN NON-WESTERN CULTURE', 'NUTR 216', 0, 'Cultural determinants influencing food habits of humans. Interrelation of eating patterns and socio-cultural, ecological, psychological and economic factors in cross-cultural settings. Roles of men and women in food provision. Lec/rec. (Bacc Core Course)', ''),
(4794, '3', 'GENERAL HUMAN NUTRITION', 'NUTR 225', 0, 'The relationship of food, its nutrients and other components to the promotion of health and fitness with emphasis on the young adult. Current health concerns on a national and international level. This course is for non-majors; NES majors and those in the health sciences should take NUTR 240.', 'Students cannot enroll who have a program in Nutrition & Food Mgt (420), Nutrition (466), Exercise and Sport Science (716) or Kinesiology (840).'),
(4795, '5', 'SCIENCE OF FOODS', 'NUTR 235', 0, 'Composition, functional properties, and structure of foods, including modified ingredients. Principles underlying preparation of food products of standard quality. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: CH 123 or 223 or ((CH 263, 263H or 273) and (CH 233 or 233H)).A minimum grade of C- is required in CH 123, CH 223, CH 263, CH 263H, CH 273, CH 233 and CH 233H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Dietetics (419).'),
(4796, '3', 'HUMAN NUTRITION', 'NUTR 240', 0, 'An introductory nutrition course for exercise science, nutrition, dietetics, food science, and health science majors who have taken general chemistry. Concepts of nutrient metabolism and utilization, nutrient deficiencies and toxicities and their relationship to disease prevention and treatment.', 'Prerequisites: (CH 121 or 224H or (CH 221, 231 or 231H)).A minimum grade of C- is required in CH 121, CH 224H, CH 221, CH 231 and CH 231H.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Food Science and Technology (135)Nutrition (426)Pre-Health Management & Policy (462)Nutrition (466)Kinesiology (840)'),
(4797, '1', 'APPLICATIONS IN HUMAN NUTRITION', 'NUTR 241', 0, 'Application of nutrition theory from NUTR 240 using a dietary project and hands-on recitation activities. A key focus of the course will be on applying nutrition theory. Rec.', 'Prerequisite: NUTR 240*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in NUTR 240.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in:Nutrition (426)Nutrition (466)Pre-Dietetics (652)Exercise and Sport Science (716)Kinesiology (840)'),
