(4801, '4', 'FOODSERVICE PRODUCTION AND PURCHASING', 'NUTR 311', 0, 'Food production, purchasing, facility and materials management in foodservice operations. Quantity production styles, safety and sanitation, service methods and equipment. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisite: NUTR 235.A minimum grade of C- is required in NUTR 235.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Nutrition and Foodservice Sys (261) or Dietetics (419).'),
(4802, '3', '*ISSUES IN NUTRITION AND HEALTH', 'NUTR 312', 0, 'Impact of nutrition as one component of complex environmental, behavioral, social, and genetic factors significant to health promotion. Apply scientific knowledge to current health issues of changing dietary patterns, technological development in food products and nutrition controversies. Recognize economic and public policy implications. Lec/rec. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Prerequisites: NUTR 225 or 240.A minimum grade of C- is required in NUTR 225 and NUTR 240.'),
(4803, '3', 'PROMOTING FOOD AND NUTRITION', 'NUTR 319', 0, 'Strategies in promoting products, services or ideas; negotiating, advertising, public policy, consumer service, social marketing, market research, trends and strategies. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: NUTR 240 and 241.A minimum grade of C- is required in NUTR 240 and NUTR 241.'),
(4804, '3', 'NUTRITION THROUGH THE LIFE CYCLE', 'NUTR 325', 0, 'Nutritional needs and concerns in pregnancy and lactation, infancy, childhood, adolescence, adult and later years.', 'Prerequisites: (NUTR 240 or 225) and NUTR 241.A minimum grade of C- is required in NUTR 240, NUTR 225 and NUTR 241.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Nutrition (426) or Nutrition (466).'),
(4805, '4', 'NUTRITION FOR EXERCISE', 'NUTR 341', 0, 'Review of the interrelationship between nutrition and exercise, including macronutrient, micronutrient and fluid needs for active individuals. CROSSLISTED as KIN 341/NUTR 341.', 'Prerequisites: KIN 324 and NUTR 240.A minimum grade of C- is required in KIN 324 and NUTR 240.'),
