(4819, '4', 'MEDICAL NUTRITION THERAPY I', 'NUTR 430', 0, 'Principles and practices related to implementation and documentation of the nutrition care process in dietetics. Diet-related conditions are addressed during the three-course sequence using lecture, case studies and assessment recitation sessions. Lec/lab/rec.', 'Prerequisites: (BB 350 or (BB 450 and 451)) and (BI 233 or 332) and (BI 242 or 342) and (BI 233 or 333) and (BI 243 or 343) and NUTR 417* and 439.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in BB 350, BB 450, BB 451, BI 233, BI 332, BI 242, BI 342, BI 333, BI 243, BI 343, NUTR 417 and NUTR 439.Students cannot enroll who have a program in Pre-Dietetics (652).'),
