(5402, '3', 'QUANTUM MECHANICS', 'PH 651', 2, 'Basic principles of nonrelativistic quantum theory and applications. Schroedinger theory, quantum theory of angular momentum, matrix mechanics, perturbation theory, identical particles, scattering.', ''),
(5403, '3', 'ADVANCED QUANTUM THEORY', 'PH 654', 2, 'Scattering theory, second quantization and many body theory, relativistic quantum mechanics, quantization of fields, quantum electrodynamics, and elementary particles.', ''),
(5404, '3', 'ATOMIC, MOLECULAR, OPTICAL PHYSICS, SEMICONDUCTOR OPTICS', 'PH 682', 2, 'Linear response theory; polarization effects; interband excitations and emissions; low dimensional systems; excitons; phonons; semiconductor lasers; photovoltaics. Not offered every year.', ''),
(5405, '2', 'ATOMIC, MOLECULAR AND OPTICAL PHYSICS, NONLINEAR OPTICS', 'PH 683', 2, 'Coherent nonlinear electromagnetic phenomena; harmonic generation and parametric mixing; quantum mechanical description of multi-photon interactions; incoherent multi-photon interactions; coherent nonlinear optical phenomena and spectroscopies. Offered in alternate years.', ''),
