(5410, '1', 'PLANT GENETICS RECITATION', 'PBG 431', 0, 'Review and demonstration of plant genetics principles.', ''),
(5411, '4', 'PLANT TISSUE CULTURE', 'PBG 441', 0, 'Principles, methods, and applications of plant tissue culture. Laboratory is important part of course. Topics include callus culture, regeneration, somaclonal variation, micropropagation, anther culture, somatic hybridization, and transformation. CROSSLISTED as PBG 441 and MCB 541/PBG 541.', ''),
(5412, '4', 'PLANT BREEDING', 'PBG 450', 0, 'An introduction to the genetic improvement of self-pollinated, cross-pollinated, and asexually propagated species and the genetic principles on which breeding methods are based. Examples are drawn from a wide range of crops, including cereal grains, grasses, fruits, nuts, and vegetables; guest lecturers discuss their breeding programs. Additional topics include crop evaluation, germplasm preservation, disease resistance, and biotechnology. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisite: PBG 430.A minimum grade of D- is required in PBG 430.'),
