(5630, '1 to 12', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERNSHIP/ EOH', 'H 410', 0, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisite: H 407.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 407.Enrollment limited to students with a term level of Junior or Senior.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Environmental Safety & Health (704) or Environmental & Occupat Health (747).'),
(5631, '1 to 12', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERNSHIP/ HMP', 'H 410', 0, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisite: H 407.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 407.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Health Management and Policy (242).'),
(5632, '1 to 12', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERNSHIP/ HPHB', 'H 410', 0, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisite: H 407.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 407.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Health Promo and Hlth Behavior (241).'),
(5633, '1 to 12', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERNSHIP/ESH', 'H 410', 0, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisite: H 407.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 407.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Environmental Safety & Health (704) or Environmental & Occupat Health (747).'),
(5634, '1 to 12', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERNSHIP/HPHB', 'H 410', 0, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Prerequisite: H 407.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 407.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Health Promo and Hlth Behavior (241).'),
(5635, '3', 'FOUNDATIONS OF EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 425', 0, 'Measures of disease frequency; measures of effect; association and causation; sources of inaccuracy; experimental and observational study designs. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: H 220, ST 201, 314 or 351.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 220, ST 201, ST 314 and ST 351.'),
(5636, '3', 'ECONOMIC ISSUES IN HEALTH AND MEDICAL CARE', 'H 432', 0, 'Application of economic principles to the health care field: the demand for medical care and insurance, health care suppliers, health care markets.', 'Prerequisites: (ECON 201 or 201H) and H 210.A minimum grade of C- is required in ECON 201, ECON 201H and H 210.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (239).'),
(5637, '3', '^HEALTH CARE LAW AND REGULATION', 'H 434', 0, 'Legal aspects of health care delivery; tort law and its applications; professional liability and liability insurance; laws relative to health care institutions, cost controls, antitrust and access. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisites: H 210, 250 and WR 222.A minimum grade of C is required in H 210.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 250 and WR 222.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (239).'),
(5638, '3', 'ADVANCED TOPICS IN HEALTH CARE MANAGEMENT', 'H 436', 0, 'Covers how health services are governed and organized; how health care organizations assess and adapt to change; constraints/opportunities in shaping organizational performance; leadership; strategic decision-making and the use of evidence-based management in health care.', 'Prerequisites: H 210 and 250.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 210 and H 250.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Health Management and Policy (242) or Health Management and Policy (465).'),
(5639, '3', '*OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH', 'H 445', 0, 'Current and historical topics in the area of occupational health, with particular emphasis on the types of materials that produce human health effects; clinical and epidemiologic data used to assess the public health importance of occupational pollutants and to evaluate control strategies. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(5640, '3', 'PUBLIC HEALTH TOXICOLOGY', 'H 448', 0, 'Introduction to the concepts and principles of toxicology as they apply to environmental and occupational health', 'Prerequisite: H 344.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 344.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(5641, '3', 'FINANCIAL MANAGEMENT OF HEALTH CARE ORGANIZATIONS', 'H 457', 0, 'Utilization of standard financial tools needed to manage the capital resources of health care organizations. Includes funding capital projects, product costing, budgeting methods, capital formation and investment strategies.', 'Prerequisites: BA 215, H 210 and 250.A minimum grade of C- is required in BA 215, H 210 and H 250.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (239) or Health Management and Policy (465).'),
(5642, '3', 'REIMBURSEMENT MECHANISMS', 'H 458', 0, 'Introduces and analyzes the different types of healthcare reimbursement methodologies used in the U.S. health care system.', 'Prerequisite: H 210.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 210.'),
(5643, '4', '^PLANNING AND EVALUATING HEALTH PROMOTION PROGRAMS', 'H 476', 0, 'A systematic approach to planning, implementing and evaluating health promotion programs in a variety of health related settings. Students will be writing a series of drafts to effectively develop a health promotion program plan. (Writing Intensive Course)', 'Prerequisites: H 225, 320 and 376.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 225, H 320 and H 376.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (239) or Public Health (496).'),
(5644, '1', 'UNDERGRADUATE EOH SEMINAR', 'H 480', 0, 'Explores current topics in environmental health and safety. EOH faculty will discuss their current research interests; EOH graduate student speakers will share their environmental health and safety internship experiences. Documentaries will be viewed to introduce topics of discussion. Features will be discussions relating directly to ongoing, current environmental/occupational health crises, both in the United States and around the world. Graded P/N.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Environmental Safety & Health (704) or Environmental & Occupat Health (747).'),
(5645, '3', 'EMERGENCY AND DISASTER MANAGEMENT', 'H 489', 0, 'Study of preparedness, response, recovery and business resumption strategies, activities and applications needed to effectively deal with emergency and disaster incidents.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(5646, '3', 'APPLIED ERGONOMICS', 'H 494', 0, 'Principles of occupational ergonomics for managing optimal worker performance and well-being.', ''),
