(5652, '1 to 16', 'PRACTICUM', 'H 509', 2, 'Supervised work experience in a public health or health care administration setting. Open to majors in public health. Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the College of Health & Human Sci or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
(5653, '1 to 16', 'INTERNSHIP', 'H 510', 2, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).'),
(5654, '1 to 16', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERN/ MASTER PUBLIC HEALTH', 'H 510', 2, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', ''),
(5655, '1 to 16', 'INTERNSHIP: INTERN/MASTER OF PUBLIC HEALTH', 'H 510', 2, 'Directed field experience with participation in a community, worksite, or health agency program. Experience is individually arranged to meet student needs. Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5656, '3', 'COMMUNITY, CULTURE, AND GLOBAL HEALTH', 'H 511', 2, 'Overview of health issues across cultures, ethnic groups, and regional/national boundaries from a critical and interdisciplinary perspective. Special emphasis on understanding social and behavioral factors that influence health in underserved communities/groups, especially ethnic/racial minorities, women, children, and migrants.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5657, '3', 'INTRODUCTION TO ENVIRONMENTAL AND OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH SCIENCES', 'H 512', 2, 'Introduction to environmental and occupational health. Hazards affecting human health are examined in the context of current social, political and regulatory pressures.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5658, '12', 'INTEGRATED APPROACH TO PUBLIC HEALTH', 'H 513', 2, 'An integrated approach to introduce students to the core knowledge and methods used in public health, including evidence-based approaches to public health, public health and health care systems, planning and management to promote health, and policy in public health.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).Enrollment limited to students in a Master of Public Health degree.'),
(5659, '1', 'ENVIRONMENT, SAFETY AND HEALTH SEMINAR', 'H 514', 2, 'One-credit graduate seminar on current topics of interest and importance to the environmental health and occupational safety field. Critical reading of research publications, discussion of controversial issues facing ESH professionals, and/or presentation of current ESH research.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5660, '3', 'RESEARCH METHODS IN SOCIAL AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SCIENCES', 'H 515', 2, 'Provides an introduction to quantitative research methods and design. Topics include definition of research problems and questions, hypothesis generation, research design, sampling, variable definition and measurement, data collection, and ethical considerations. Also provides a brief introduction to qualitative and mixed methods.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Human Development & Family Stu (4470) or Public Health (7580).'),
(5661, '3', 'RESEARCH METHODS IN GLOBAL HEALTH', 'H 516', 2, 'Overview of research methods used to understand health, illness, health care, and health-seeking behavior in international settings. Special emphasis on the use of qualitative and mixed methods in international health research.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
(5662, '3', 'PUBLIC HEALTH ETHICS AND ISSUES', 'H 518', 2, 'Explores key ethical issues in the context of public health practice; codes and guidelines for ethical conduct of public health practice; issues related to social accountability, vulnerable populations, and ethical framework for community engagement.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5663, '3', 'DISPLACEMENT, MIGRATION, AND GLOBAL HEALTH', 'H 519', 2, 'Critical examination of health of displaced/migrant populations with an emphasis on health disparities and social determinants. Understanding intersections of humanitarianism, migration, vulnerability, and displacement from a global health perspective.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5664, '3', 'HEALTH DISPARITIES', 'H 520', 2, 'Health disparities based on race/ethnicity, culture, social class, and rural/urban residence, among others; strategies to reduce disparities, promote health, and prevent disease in diverse populations.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5665, '4', 'FOUNDATIONS OF PUBLIC HEALTH', 'H 523', 2, 'Fundamental principles, concepts and tools used in public health to promote the health of populations. Using a combination of case study method, lecture and discussion, students will develop a broad understanding of public health and recognition of how discipline-specializations address the social, behavioral and environmental determinants of public health.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Athletic Training (2440) or Adapted Physical Education (3010).'),
(5666, '4', 'INTRODUCTION TO BIOSTATISTICS', 'H 524', 2, 'Quantitative analysis and interpretation of health data including probability distributions, estimation of effects, and hypothesis-tests such as Chi-square, one-way ANOVA, and simple linear regression.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5667, '3', 'EPIDEMIOLOGICAL METHODS I', 'H 525', 2, 'Introduction to the concepts and methods of epidemiology. Topics include measures of population health, screening, study design, measures of association, and interpretation of epidemiological data.', 'Prerequisites: H 513 or 535.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513 and H 535.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5668, '3', 'EPIDEMIOLOGIC METHODS II', 'H 526', 2, 'Concepts and methods of epidemiological analysis; standardization; stratified analysis; confounding and its control; planning and conducting epidemiologic research; role of multivariate analysis in epidemiologic research.', 'Prerequisites: H 524 and 525.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 524 and H 525.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5669, '3', 'CRITICAL ASSESSMENT OF INTERNATIONAL HEALTH PROGRAMS', 'H 527', 2, 'Introduces the critical evaluation framework of assessing international health development programs, based on self-determination and community ownership principles. The framework of assessment method includes three levels: upstream evaluation, midstream evaluation, and downstream evaluation.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5670, '3', 'GLOBAL HEALTH ISSUES', 'H 528', 2, 'Examines major issues in health developments of global significance, their causes and impacts on international health, and methods and strategies to address them.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5671, '3', 'INTERNATIONAL HEALTH', 'H 529', 2, 'Overview of the epidemiological, economic, political, sociological, and cultural factors that impact on international health. Special emphasis on the methods of prevention/intervention utilized in coping with health problems on an international level.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5672, '3', 'HEALTH POLICY ANALYSIS AND POLITICS', 'H 530', 2, 'Examination of current health policy issues affecting health care programs, services, and organization as well as the role of politics in public health and health policy. Exploration of processes by which health policy proposals are generated, promoted, defeated, modified and implemented.', 'Prerequisites: H 513 or HHS 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513 and HHS 514.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5673, '3', 'ECONOMIC ISSUES IN HEALTH AND MEDICAL CARE', 'H 532', 2, 'Application of economics principles to the health care field: the demand for medical care and insurance, health care suppliers, health care markets.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5674, '3', 'HEALTH SYSTEMS ORGANIZATION', 'H 533', 2, 'Examines the nature of health and health care services and reviews the role of government and the free market on health services. Alternative ways of organizing, financing, and delivery of health care services are explored.', ''),
(5675, '3', 'HEALTH CARE LAW AND REGULATION', 'H 534', 2, 'Legal aspects of health care delivery; tort law and its applications; professional liability and liability insurance; laws relative to health care institutions, cost controls, antitrust and access.', ''),
(5676, '3', 'HEALTHCARE ORGANIZATION LEADERSHIP THEORY AND BEHAVIOR', 'H 536', 2, 'Overview of organization theory and behavior in health care organizations. Emphasis is on developing an understanding of the factors and forces that influence the structures, behaviors, and operations of health care delivery organizations. This understanding will be developed through consideration of organizations, their environments, and the roles of individuals working in management.', 'Prerequisites: H 513 or HHS 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513 and HHS 514.Enrollment is limited to Graduate or Non-Degree / Credential level students.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
(5677, '3', 'INJURY EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 537', 2, 'An overview of the distribution and determinants of injuries, methodological issues specific to injury epidemiology, and approaches to injury control.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, 525, 535 or HHS 513.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, H 525, H 535 and HHS 513.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5678, '3', 'AIR QUALITY AND HUMAN HEALTH', 'H 541', 2, 'Examination of the major sources of air pollution, its impact on ecosystems and climate change, and population health. Will also discuss technologies and introduce regulations that are used to control air pollutants.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5679, '4', 'EXPOSURE SCIENCE I', 'H 543', 2, 'Overview of the concepts, principles and practices in modern environmental and occupational exposure assessment. Exposure Science I provides a broad introduction to environmental and occupational exposure assessment methods, while Exposure Science II focuses on sampling and measurement methods.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5680, '3', 'PHYSICAL AGENTS AND HUMAN HEALTH', 'H 546', 2, 'Focus on physical agents (heat, noise, vibration, radiation) and health risks associated with these agents. It covers the range and sources of exposure to physical agents, methods of characterizing these exposures, effects on human health, and the regulations/standards that set limits for physical agents. Lec/lab.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5681, '4', 'GIS AND PUBLIC HEALTH', 'H 547', 2, 'Applications of geographic information systems (GIS) to public health are reviewed, including mapping, spatial analysis methods, estimating access, and exposure assessment. This course is geared toward individuals involved in public health who have no (or introductory level) knowledge of GIS. Lec/lab.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5682, '3', 'PUBLIC HEALTH TOXICOLOGY', 'H 548', 2, 'Introduction to the concepts and principles of toxicology as they apply to environmental and occupational health.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5683, '3', 'MASS MEDIA AND HEALTH', 'H 549', 2, 'Examines the effects of mass media on population health, from the negative impact of advertising of cigarettes, alcohol and junk food, to the (hopefully) positive impact of public health campaigns.', 'Prerequisite: H 571.A minimum grade of C is required in H 571.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5684, '3', 'APPLIED EPIDEMIOLOGICAL ANALYSIS OF SECONDARY DATA', 'H 551', 2, 'Practical experience performing a hypothesis-driven epidemiological analysis utilizing secondary surveillance or other appropriate data set, writing an analytical plan, appropriate programming for the analysis (using STATA or SAS), understanding the analysis output, preparing tables, and interpreting results.', 'Prerequisites: H 526, 560 and 580.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 526, H 560 and H 580.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5685, '3', 'DISASTER EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 552', 2, 'Describe the impact of natural and manmade disasters on human health, understand epidemiologic methods specific to disasters, and apply fundamental epidemiologic methods to identify and characterize disaster-related adverse health outcomes.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, 525, 535 or HHS 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, H 525, H 535 and HHS 514.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5686, '3', 'EPIDEMIOLOGY OF AGING', 'H 554', 2, 'An overview of the core principles of the epidemiology of aging is provided. There will be an emphasis on health and disease processes in older adults. Students will learn essential study design and analytic issues that may arise in studies of aging.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, 525, 535 or HHS 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, H 525, H 535 and HHS 514.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5687, '3', 'CANCER EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 555', 2, 'Introduction to basic concepts and methodology in cancer epidemiology.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, HHS 514, H 525 or 535.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, HHS 514, H 525 and H 535.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5688, '3', 'REIMBURSEMENT MECHANISMS', 'H 558', 2, 'Techniques used in cost-effectiveness analysis. Examples are drawn from the public health and health economics literature.', ''),
(5689, '3', 'PUBLIC HEALTH SURVEILLANCE', 'H 560', 2, 'An introduction to public health surveillance systems (national and international) for chronic and infectious diseases. Utility of existing surveillance systems for secondary epidemiological data analysis.', 'Prerequisites: H 524 and 525.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 524 and H 525.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5690, '3', 'INFECTIOUS DISEASE EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 562', 2, 'Understand epidemiologic methods specific to infectious diseases, apply fundamental epidemiologic methods to infectious disease questions, and describe the broad trends in global infectious disease burden. The application methods and principles will be explored through lectures, discussions, assignments and writing projects.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, 525, 535 or 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, H 525, H 535 and H 514.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5691, '3', 'PHYSICAL ACTIVITY EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 563', 2, 'Physical activity epidemiology will focus on current research, controversial issues, and methodological problems in the epidemiology of physical activity, exercise, and health.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, HHS 514, H 525 or 535.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, HHS 514, H 525 and H 535.'),
(5692, '3', 'COMPUTING TOOLS AND HEALTH DATA ANALYSIS', 'H 564', 2, 'Modern computational  biostatistics for analyzing health data, emphasizing important technologies and methods for data processing and understanding of how they work. Topics will evolve over time as new procedures are developed.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5693, '3', 'PRINCIPLES OF HEALTH BEHAVIOR', 'H 571', 2, 'Theoretical approaches to behavior change in health promotion/education research and practice; factors influencing health behaviors, ethical behavior change issues, behavioral interventions for special populations.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5694, '3', 'COMMUNITY ORGANIZATION FOR HEALTH PROMOTION AND EDUCATION', 'H 572', 2, 'History, theory, and practice of community organizing for health advocacy; focus on group processes, use of media, leadership, coalitions, grass roots methods and social change.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5695, '3', 'EVALUATION OF HEALTH PROMOTION AND EDUCATION PROGRAMS', 'H 575', 2, 'Provides theoretical and practical bases for program evaluation. Develops basic skills in a variety of approaches to evaluation, including techniques that are particularly suitable for evaluating health promotion, community health improvement, and related health and social services programs. Course learning is synthesized through designing an evaluation framework and methodology for a relevant program.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, 515 or HHS 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, H 515 and HHS 514.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5696, '4', 'PROGRAM PLANNING FOR HEALTH/HUMAN SERVICES', 'H 576', 2, 'Provides students with an introduction to the principles of program planning and the development of program plans, with a focus on evidence-based public health/human services. Students will have the opportunity to integrate skills developed through prior courses in the context of writing a program plan.', 'Prerequisites: (H 515 or HHS 514) and H 571 and 575.A minimum grade of C- is required in H 515, HHS 514, H 571 and H 575.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).'),
(5697, '4', 'LINEAR REGRESSION AND ANALYSIS OF TIME TO EVENT DATA', 'H 580', 2, 'Multiple linear regression analysis for measurement data and survival analysis methods for time to event health data, including modes of inference, diagnostics, model selection, and reporting conclusions. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (H 524 or HDFS 530).A minimum grade of C is required in H 524 and HDFS 530.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
(5698, '4', 'GENERALIZED LINEAR MODELS AND CATEGORICAL DATA ANALYSIS', 'H 581', 2, 'Biostatistical methods focusing on binary and count data will provide a foundation for understanding and implementing generalized linear regression and categorical data models that are commonly used to analyze epidemiological and public health data from cohort, case-control, and clinical trial study designs. Lec/lab.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5699, '3', 'ANALYSIS OF CORRELATED HEALTH DATA', 'H 582', 2, 'Biostatistical methods for clustered, repeated measures, and longitudinal correlated health data, with an introduction to applications of linear and generalized linear mixed models and generalized estimating equations.', 'Prerequisite: H 581.A minimum grade of C is required in H 581.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5700, '4', 'ENVIRONMENTAL AND OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH AND SAFETY MANAGEMENT', 'H 583', 2, 'Studies the design and management principles and practices in the environment, safety and health field.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5701, '3', 'ENVIRONMENT, SAFETY AND HEALTH POLICY AND LAW', 'H 585', 2, 'Survey of the environment, safety and health policy and law in the United States. Furnishes the basic knowledge and general understanding about policy and law-related issues important to all environmental health and safety professionals.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5702, '3', 'APPLIED OCCUPATIONAL SAFETY AND HEALTH', 'H 588', 2, 'The management and technical aspects of a workplace safety and health program are identified and assessed. Students completing the course receive a 30-hour OSHA General Industry card.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5703, '3', 'EMERGENCY AND DISASTER MANAGEMENT', 'H 589', 2, 'Study of preparedness, response, recovery and business resumption strategies, activities and applications needed to effectively deal with emergency and disaster incidents.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5704, '3', 'OCCUPATIONAL ERGONOMICS AND BIOMECHANICS', 'H 590', 2, 'Examines the advanced theories, applications, and contemporary topics of occupational ergonomics and biomechanics. Topics include muscle physiology, work-related musculoskeletal disorders, assessing biomechanical exposure in the workplace, various material handling assessment tools, 3-Dimensional Static Strength Prediction Program, human vibrations, and implementing ergonomic interventions.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5705, '3', 'REPRODUCTIVE EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 593', 2, 'Focuses on current research, controversial issues, and methodological problems in the epidemiology of reproductive health.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, HHS 514, H 525 or 535.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, HHS 514, H 525 and H 535.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5706, '3', 'APPLIED ERGONOMICS', 'H 594', 2, 'Principles of occupational ergonomics for managing optimal worker performance and well-being.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5707, '3', 'HEALTHCARE EPIDEMIOLOGY', 'H 596', 2, 'Focus on current research, controversial issues, and methodological problems in the epidemiology of healthcare. Topics include institutional infection control, medical errors, screening and diagnostic testing, cost-effectiveness, and others related to the delivery and assessment of healthcare, with a focus on the US healthcare system specifically.', 'Prerequisites: H 513, 525, 535 or HHS 514.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513, H 525, H 535 and HHS 514.Enrollment limited to students in the Public Health & Human Sci college.'),
(5708, '3', 'HEALTH POLICY ANALYSIS METHODS', 'H 598', 2, 'Analysis of public policies affecting health care programs, services and organizations and the impact of those programs on citizens. Health services research methods, including data sources for health policy research and health policy literature.', 'Prerequisites: H 513 and 533.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 513 and H 533.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5709, '3', 'SPECIAL TOPICS: ST/ HLTH LEADERSHP INNOVATION', 'H 599', 2, '', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5710, '1', 'SPECIAL TOPICS: ST/EPI PROFESSIONAL SEMINAR', 'H 599', 2, '', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5711, '1 to 16', 'RESEARCH AND SCHOLARSHIP', 'H 601', 2, '', ''),
(5712, '1 to 16', 'THESIS', 'H 603', 2, '', ''),
(5713, '1 to 16', 'READING AND CONFERENCE', 'H 605', 2, '', ''),
(5714, '1 to 16', 'PROJECTS', 'H 606', 2, '', ''),
(5715, '1 to 16', 'WORKSHOP', 'H 608', 2, '', ''),
(5716, '1 to 16', 'INTERNSHIP', 'H 610', 2, '', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5717, '1', 'DOCTORAL SEMINAR IN PUBLIC HEALTH: RESEARCH AND PRACTICE', 'H 612', 2, 'Contemporary research and professional issues specific to the discipline of public health. Includes responsible conduct of research, writing for publication, professional development and leadership, and faculty research in public health.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).Enrollment limited to students in a Doctor of Philosophy degree.'),
(5718, '1 to 9', 'INDEPENDENT RESEARCH PROJECT', 'H 613', 2, 'Independent research project for PhD students, including research design, execution or research, and the formal presentation of findings in written form. Student will develop an original research topic based on knowledge and review of the literature in a public health-relevant area of inquiry. Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).'),
(5719, '4', 'RESEARCH MANUSCRIPT', 'H 614', 2, 'PhD students write a manuscript to submit to a peer-reviewed journal as part of the course requirements. Graded P/N.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).'),
(5720, '3', 'ADV TPCS/GLBL HLTH INTERV/PRAC: AT/GLBL HLTH SYS INTVN & PRACT', 'H 620', 2, 'Examines the processes and tools involved in planning and evaluating culturally competent health and human service prevention and intervention programs in the global context. Special considerations in program decision-making in the global context (community engagement, cultural competence, sustainability, feasibility, political/ethical issues) will be explored. Provides a key forum for doctoral students to share ongoing developments in their research and practice drawing from fieldwork as well as attended conferences and meetings.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5721, '4', 'QUANTITATIVE HEALTH POLICY RESEARCH METHODS I', 'H 630', 2, 'Contemporary doctoral-level quantitative health policy/services research methods emphasizing linear regression models, data sources for health policy research, and health policy research literature.', 'Prerequisite: H 524.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 524.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Public Health (7580).'),
(5722, '3', 'REPORT RESULTS: WRIT FOR EPI: REPORT RESULTS: WRIT FOR EPID', 'H 650', 2, 'Applied experience writing a scientific paper to disseminate results, including deciding on authorship, preparing a lay summary, revising and responding to peer review, and serving as a reviewer.', 'Prerequisites: H 526, 551 and 580.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 526, H 551 and H 580.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5723, '4', 'QUANTITATIVE HEALTH POLICY RESEARCH METHODS II', 'H 659', 2, 'Advanced doctoral-level quantitative health policy/services research methods emphasizing health care utilization, expenditures, and outcomes data.', 'Prerequisite: H 630.A minimum grade of B- is required in H 630.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5724, '3', 'ADVANCED THEORIES OF HEALTH BEHAVIOR', 'H 671', 2, 'Provides an in-depth examination of major theories of health behavior (both health compromising and health enhancing).', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5725, '3', 'ADVANCED QUALITATIVE METHODS IN HEALTH BEHAVIOR', 'H 672', 2, 'Provides an in-depth examination of the use of qualitative methods in health behavior research and practice.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5726, '3', 'ADVANCED TOPICS IN HEALTH PROMOTION AND HEALTH BEHAVIOR', 'H 676', 2, 'Examines topics of relevance to health promotion and health behavior. Specific topics include current issues and emerging research findings, with a focus on social and behavior science perspectives, analysis of public health problems, and application of principles and practices of health promotion and health behavior.', 'Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(5727, '4', 'SPECIAL STUDIES: SS/ DOCTORAL GRANT WRITING SEM', 'H 699', 2, '', 'Enrollment limited to students in a Doctor of Philosophy degree.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Health & Human Sci or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
(5728, '4', 'SPECIAL STUDIES: SS/RESEARCH PRACTICUM', 'H 699', 2, '', ''),
(5729, '4', 'SPECIAL STUDIES: ST/ DOCTORAL GRANT WRITING', 'H 699', 2, '', 'Enrollment limited to students in a Doctor of Philosophy degree.Enrollment limited to students in the College of Health & Human Sci or Public Health & Human Sci colleges.'),
(5730, '0', 'LEADERSHIP', 'PPOL 002', 0, 'Provides students with basic personal and interpersonal leadership skills that can be used within and outside of a work setting. Through practice, the leadership experience help students explore motivation, decision-making, time management, power, team building, conflict, ethics, dealing with change, communication skills, and diversity issues.', ''),
(5731, '0', 'LEADERSHIP: LEADERSHIP/ PSLA LEADERSHIP', 'PPOL 002', 0, 'Provides students with basic personal and interpersonal leadership skills that can be used within and outside of a work setting. Through practice, the leadership experience help students explore motivation, decision-making, time management, power, team building, conflict, ethics, dealing with change, communication skills, and diversity issues.', ''),
(5732, '0', 'LEADERSHIP: LEADERSHIP:PRES ST LEGIS ADVOC', 'PPOL 002', 0, 'Provides students with basic personal and interpersonal leadership skills that can be used within and outside of a work setting. Through practice, the leadership experience help students explore motivation, decision-making, time management, power, team building, conflict, ethics, dealing with change, communication skills, and diversity issues.', ''),
