(6148, '4', 'FOUNDATIONS OF DATA ANALYTICS', 'ST 516', 2, 'Foundations of estimation and hypothesis testing; desirable properties of estimators; maximum likelihood; one- and two-sample problems; theoretical results are explored through simulations and analysis using R. Offered via Ecampus only.', ''),
(6149, '4', 'DATA ANALYTICS I', 'ST 517', 2, 'Methods for modeling quantitative data and statistical learning--simple and multiple linear regression; linear mixed effects models; data imputation; prediction and cross-validation; scaling up to large datasets. Simulations and data analysis using R. Offered via Ecampus only.', 'Prerequisite: ST 516.A minimum grade of C+ is required in ST 516.'),
(6150, '4', 'DATA ANALYTICS II', 'ST 518', 2, 'Statistical methods and data analysis techniques for count data. Topics include tests for tables of counts, logistic regression, log-linear regression, generalized linear mixed models, and issues for large datasets. Data analysis in R.', 'Prerequisite: ST 517.A minimum grade of C+ is required in ST 517.'),
