(6664, '4', 'INTRODUCTION TO SCULPTURAL WOODTURNING', 'WSE 516', 2, 'The development of studio / sculptural woodturning has a unique history, and involves a cluster of specialized skills. This course blends historic woodturning practices with modern approaches and aesthetics to bring an understanding of wood science into this very specialized field of woodturning.', 'Prerequisites: WSE 513 and 514.A minimum grade of B is required in WSE 513 and WSE 514.'),
(6665, '3', 'THE GLOBAL CONTEXT OF THE FOREST SECTOR', 'WSE 520', 2, 'Provides a broad knowledge base of business and marketing practices in the global forest industry. Includes a module on research ethics that fulfills OSU Graduate School requirements.', ''),
(6666, '4', 'WOOD SCIENCE I', 'WSE 521', 2, 'A comprehensive overview and integration of wood anatomy, wood physics, wood chemistry and wood mechanics; global contemporary issues impacting the wood and fiber sector; integration of basic wood sciences to understand the complex relationships between environment and wood material properties, and the influence of both on the use of wood-based materials.', ''),
(6667, '4', 'WOOD SCIENCE II', 'WSE 522', 2, 'Continuation of the comprehensive overview and integration of wood and fiber anatomy, physics, chemistry, and mechanics; integration of basic wood science to understand relationships with wood and fiber properties and their impact on final use. Focus on biological, chemical and physical degradation of wood; adhesion; and physical and engineering properties of wood. Lec/lab.', ''),
(6668, '3', 'FOREST PRODUCTS BUSINESS', 'WSE 553', 2, 'Provides students with the skills necessary to operate effectively in the global forest products industry.', ''),
(6669, '4', 'WOOD DESIGN', 'WSE 558', 2, 'Study of basic wood properties and design considerations. Design and behavior of wood connectors, beams, columns and beam columns. Introduction to plywood and glued laminated members. Analysis and design of structural diaphragms and shear walls. Lec/lab. CROSSLISTED as CE 584/WSE 558.', ''),
(6670, '4', 'BIO-BASED PRODUCTS MANUFACTURING', 'WSE 561', 2, 'First of a 3-term series exploring technologies and management practices associated with manufacturing products from wood and other renewable materials. Subjects covered include the major processing steps for the conversion of raw materials such as wood, bamboo, hemp, and cereal straws into products.', ''),
(6671, '4', 'ADVANCED MANUFACTURING 1', 'WSE 562', 2, 'Second of a 3-term series exploring technologies and management practices associated with manufacturing products from wood and other renewable materials. Subjects covered include process design elements, quality control, and approaches to continuous process improvement.', ''),
(6672, '3', 'BIOENERGY AND ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACT', 'WSE 573', 2, 'Explores world\'s use of woody biomass fuels, their potential to contribute to our region\'s energy supply, and conversion technologies such as direct combustion, pyrolysis, and thermochemical modification. Also examines emissions and other environmental impacts of utilizing renewable materials to generate energy and manufacture products.', ''),
(6673, '4', 'ADVANCED WOOD DESIGN', 'WSE 592', 2, 'Study of advanced concepts in wood properties and design. Design and analysis of specialty wood connectors. Design of wood members for adverse conditions including fire design. Common failure mechanisms and forensic engineering concepts. Design for durability. Lec/lab.', ''),
