(6749, '7', 'LOW-RESIDENCY MFA MENTORSHIP', 'WR 513', 2, 'Low-Residency Masters of Fine Arts Mentorship. Required course for graduate students in the Low-Residency Masters of Fine Arts in Creative Writing.', 'Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
(6750, '2', 'TEACHING PRACTICUM: ENGLISH COMPOSITION', 'WR 517', 2, 'Required practicum for graduate students teaching English Composition.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in English (8900) or Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6751, '1', 'TEACHING PRACTICUM: WR 222', 'WR 519', 2, 'This practicum prepares graduate teaching assistants to teach Writing 222 (Argumentation). It includes both theoretical and practical components, providing an overview of the curriculum and addressing course development, lesson planning, and pedagogical best practices. The practicum is required for SWLF graduate students with a focus in rhetoric and composition.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a program in English (8900), Creative Writing (8920) or Interdisciplinary Studies (9900).'),
(6752, '4', 'STUDIES IN WRITING: ST/WRITING WOMEN\'S LIVES', 'WR 520', 2, 'Selected topics in rhetoric and composition.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to Graduate level students.'),
(6753, '1', 'TEACHING PRACTICUM: FICTION WRITING', 'WR 521', 2, 'Required practicum for graduate students teaching introduction to fiction writing.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in English (8900) or Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6754, '1', 'TEACHING PRACTICUM: POETRY WRITING', 'WR 522', 2, 'Required practicum for graduate students teaching introduction to poetry writing.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in English (8900) or Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6755, '1', 'TEACHING PRACTICUM: NONFICTION WRITING', 'WR 523', 2, 'Required practicum for graduate students teaching introduction to nonfiction writing.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6756, '4', 'ADVANCED FICTION WRITING', 'WR 524', 2, 'Advanced fiction workshop with an emphasis on developing longer pieces.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6757, '4', 'ADVANCED NONFICTION WRITING', 'WR 540', 2, 'Advanced creative nonfiction workshop with an emphasis on developing longer pieces.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6758, '4', 'ADVANCED POETRY WRITING', 'WR 541', 2, 'Advanced poetry workshop.', 'Students with a term level of Freshman, Sophomore, Junior or Senior may not enroll.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Creative Writing (8920).'),
(6759, '4', 'ENVIRONMENTAL WRITING', 'WR 562', 2, 'Writing about environmental topics from multiple perspectives. Includes science journalism, research and writing on current scientific issues and controversies, and theories of rhetoric and environmentalism.', ''),
(6760, '4', 'RHETORICS OF RACE', 'WR 575', 2, 'By exploring the interrelated concepts of race, racialization, and racism, Rhetorics of Race problematizes race as a taken-for-granted phenomenon. Through reading, writing, and discussion, class participants study racial formations as historically specific and analyze contemporary forms of racism in the US. Readings and discussion pay close attention to how rhetoric and discourse have the power to reproduce and challenge white supremacy and race-based oppressions. Emphasizing the intersectionality of oppression?that racism necessarily takes place at intersections with other forms of subordination including sexism, homophobia, ablelism, etc.?Rhetorics of Race draws from Queer Black Feminism, Chican@ Feminism, and Critical Race Theory.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in:History of Science (5440)Women, Gender, and Sexuality (8008)Environmental Arts & Humanitie (8200)Women Studies (8680)English (8900)Creative Writing (8920)Applied Ethics (9580)Interdisciplinary Studies (9900)'),
(6761, '4', 'THE RHETORICAL TRADITION AND THE TEACHING OF WRITING', 'WR 593', 2, 'Major past and contemporary theories of written communication, their historical context, and their impact on writing and the teaching of writing.', 'Enrollment is limited to students with a major in English (8900).'),
