(6767, '3', '*BIODIVERSITY: CAUSES, CONSEQUENCES, AND CONSERVATION', 'Z 349', 0, 'The earth\'s biodiversity is a precious inheritance that is threatened by an unprecedented extinction crisis. This course examines the evolutionary and ecological processes that have created this unique diversity of life, the importance of biodiversity in maintaining the earth\'s ecosystems, and methods used to conserve biodiversity for future generations. (Bacc Core Course)', 'Students with a term level of Freshman may not enroll.'),
(6768, '3', 'ANIMAL BEHAVIOR', 'Z 350', 0, 'Concepts of behavior; sensory receptors, internal mechanisms governing responses; learning and habituation; social organization and communication.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.'),
(6769, '3', 'INVERTEBRATE BIOLOGY', 'Z 361', 0, 'Exploration of the diversity and evolutionary relationships among major invertebrate phyla with an emphasis on morphological features, functional aspects, and life history for each phylum.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.'),
(6770, '2', 'INVERTEBRATE BIOLOGY LABORATORY', 'Z 362', 0, 'Morphology and anatomy of representative invertebrates introduced in Z 361; diversity within phyla. Study is by dissections and both microscopic and macroscopic examination; field trip fee. Lab fee. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H) and Z 361*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H and Z 361.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Biology (509) or Zoology (620).'),
(6771, '3', 'VERTEBRATE BIOLOGY', 'Z 371', 0, 'Overview of vertebrate origins and phylogeny integrating several disciplines (anatomy, ecology, genetics, developmental biology, physiology, behavior, and evolution) to explore the structural and functional adaptations and evolutionary history of vertebrates. Lec.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.'),
(6772, '2', 'VERTEBRATE BIOLOGY LABORATORY', 'Z 372', 0, 'Classification, identification, and natural history of vertebrates. Includes laboratory examination of specimens and frequent field trips (fee charged) emphasizing Oregon fauna. Lab fee.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206) and Z 371*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.A minimum grade of D- is required in Z 371.Enrollment is limited to students with a major in Biology (509) or Zoology (620).'),
(6773, '5', 'COMPARATIVE/FUNCTIONAL VERTEBRATE ANATOMY', 'Z 422', 0, 'Phylogenetically-based study of the form and function of vertebrate organ systems, including integumentary, musculoskeletal, cardiopulmonary, digestive, and sensory. Lab emphasizes comparative form through dissection, and function through non-invasive experimentation. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H) and (CH 332* or 335*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213 and BI 213H.A minimum grade of D- is required in CH 332 and CH 335.'),
(6774, '3', 'ENVIRONMENTAL PHYSIOLOGY', 'Z 423', 0, 'Comparative environmental physiology of animals with emphasis on adaptations to such aspects of the physical environment as temperature, water, ions, and gases. Consideration given to interactions between physiology and environment that influence the local and geographic distribution of animals.', 'Prerequisites: (((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206)) and (CH 123 or (CH 233 or 233H) and (CH 263 or 263H)).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205, BI 206, CH 123, CH 233, CH 233H, CH 263 and CH 263H.'),
(6775, '5', 'EMBRYOLOGY AND DEVELOPMENT', 'Z 425', 0, 'An integrated molecular, cellular and whole organism approach. Comparative embryonic development from gametogenesis, body axis specification, pattern formation and organogenesis. Experimental approaches uncovering cellular interactions, regulation of gene expression, and cellular differentiation. Lab emphasizes experimental comparative developmental biology and embryology. Lab fee. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 311 or 311H) and (BI 314, 314H, BB 314 or 314H).A minimum grade of D- is required in BI 311, BI 311H, BI 314, BI 314H, BB 314 and BB 314H.Students with a term level of Freshman or Sophomore may not enroll.'),
(6776, '4', 'VERTEBRATE PHYSIOLOGY I', 'Z 431', 0, 'Systems/concepts covered include motor reflexes, autonomic nervous system, digestion/metabolism, renal and osmoregulatory, endocrine and reproductive systems. First in Z 431, Z 432/Z 442 series. Lec/rec.', 'Prerequisites: (BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H) and (CH 332* or 335*).* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, CH 332 and CH 335.'),
(6777, '3', 'VERTEBRATE PHYSIOLOGY II', 'Z 432', 0, 'Systems/concepts covered include blood, immune, lymphatic, cardiovascular, and pulmonary. Second in the Z431, 432/442 series.', 'Prerequisite: Z 431.A minimum grade of C- is required in Z 431.'),
(6778, '3', 'BEHAVIORAL NEUROBIOLOGY', 'Z 438', 0, 'An introduction to the neurobiological basis of animal behavior. Examines behavior in the context of sensory physiology, motor control, neural circuity, and cellular processes. Lec.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H) or (BI 204, 205 and 206)) and (CH 123 or (CH 233 or 233H) and (CH 263 or 263H)).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205, BI 206, CH 123, CH 233, CH 233H, CH 263 and CH 263H.'),
(6779, '2', 'VERTEBRATE PHYSIOLOGY LABORATORY', 'Z 442', 0, 'Experiments and exercises in vertebrate physiology covering systems studied in Z 431 and Z 432. Available to Biology majors. Lab fee.', 'Prerequisites: Z 431 and 432*.* May be taken concurrently.A minimum grade of C- is required in Z 431 and Z 432.Enrollment is limited to students with a program in Biology (509).'),
(6780, '4', 'MARINE AND ESTUARINE INVERTEBRATE ZOOLOGY', 'Z 461', 0, 'Comparative survey of eight major invertebrate phyla and many lesser-known phyla. Areas of emphasis will be 1) invertebrate identification, 2) natural history (diversity, habitat, feeding, behavior), and 3) comparative anatomy (adaptive significance of morphological structures). Laboratories and field trips will strongly supplement lecture material. Lec/lab. Taught at Hatfield Marine Science Center.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.'),
(6781, '4', 'HERPETOLOGY', 'Z 473', 0, 'Exploration of global herpetofauna focusing on taxa of the Pacific Northwest of North America. Identification and natural history of amphibians and reptiles are emphasized, along with a phylogenetic framework, to explore and discuss ideas involving their behavior, evolution, ecology, and conservation. Student projects examine important topics in the field.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.'),
(6782, '4', 'AQUATIC ENTOMOLOGY', 'Z 477', 0, 'Biology, ecology, collection, and identification of aquatic insects. Two required Saturday field trips. Lec/lab.', 'Prerequisites: ((BI 211 or 211H) and (BI 212 or 212H) and (BI 213 or 213H)) or (BI 204, 205 and 206).A minimum grade of C- is required in BI 211, BI 211H, BI 212, BI 212H, BI 213, BI 213H, BI 204, BI 205 and BI 206.Enrollment limited to students in the Oregon State - Cascades campus.'),
