(6789, '4', 'SECOND-YEAR AMERICAN SIGN LANGUAGE', 'ASL 212', 0, 'A continuation of the second-year ASL series with the further development of structures, receptive/expressive skills and vocabulary. Native and/or bilingual speakers of ASL will not receive credit for ASL 211, ASL 212, ASL 213.', 'Prerequisite: ASL 211.A minimum grade of D- is required in ASL 211.Enrollment limited to students in the Dist. Degree Corvallis Student campus.'),
